title: Principal Insurance Officer ‚Äì AB Rwanda Plc
description:
Job Vacancy: Principal Insurance Officer ‚Äì AB Rwanda Plc

Location: Rwanda
Job Type: Full-Time
Deadline: 5th January 2026

Job Overview

AB Rwanda Plc is seeking a qualified, competent, and experienced professional to fill the position of Principal Insurance Officer. The successful candidate will play a key role in managing and growing the Bank‚Äôs Bancassurance business while ensuring compliance with regulatory requirements and delivering excellent customer service.

Key Responsibilities & Duties

  • Solicit and procure insurance business on behalf of the Bancassurance agent.

  • Clearly explain insurance products and services to prospective policyholders without misrepresentation.

  • Assess customer needs and recommend suitable insurance plans.

  • Inform prospective policyholders of applicable insurance premiums.

  • Explain proposal form requirements and the importance of full disclosure of material facts.

  • Collect and submit all required documents to insurers and inform clients of proposal acceptance or rejection.

  • Assist policyholders, claimants, or beneficiaries during claims processing and settlement.

  • Notify insurers of any adverse habits, inconsistent income, or material facts that may affect underwriting decisions.

  • Identify oneself to prospective policyholders, insured persons, and insurers as required.

  • Ensure compliance with internal policies and procedures in all Bancassurance services.

  • Lead the development of the Bancassurance strategy and advise Management on execution and monitoring.

  • Supervise daily Bancassurance operations including cross-selling, risk posting, claims administration, and documentation.

  • Supervise specified persons involved in Bancassurance activities.

  • Resolve customer inquiries promptly in line with policies and procedures.

  • Manage correspondence with insurance companies.

  • Represent the Bank at conferences, business meetings, and industry events.

  • Perform any other duties assigned by Management.

Reporting Responsibilities

  • Prepare and reconcile insurance premiums payable to insurers.

  • Prepare and submit regulatory reports to the Central Bank, including but not limited to:

    • Gross premiums collected (life and non-life) per insurance class

    • Commission received or receivable per insurance class

    • Number of policies in force, cancelled, lapsed, or terminated

    • Claims reported and customer complaints received

    • Fraud incidents encountered

    • Remedial actions taken to address customer complaints

Qualifications, Skills & Experience

  • Bachelor‚Äôs degree in Business Administration, Insurance, Finance, Accounting, Actuarial Science, or a related field.

  • Minimum of three (3) years‚Äô experience as an insurance underwriter, claims officer, or sales officer.

  • Completion of foundation courses provided by ASSAR or CII (Diploma is an added advantage).

  • Strong communication skills.

  • Excellent planning and organizational abilities.

  • High attention to detail.

  • Strong problem-solving skills.

How to Apply

Interested candidates should send ONLY the following documents:

  • Letter of Interest

  • Curriculum Vitae (CV)

  • Copy of academic qualifications

  • Copy of National ID

üìß Email: abr-recruiting@abr.rw
‚è∞ Deadline: 5th January 2026

Important:

  • Please clearly state ‚ÄúPrincipal Insurance Officer‚Äù in the subject line of your email.

  • Only shortlisted candidates will be contacted.

title: Officer, Guarantee Risk at Development Bank of Rwanda (BRD)
description:
VACANCY ANNOUNCEMENT

The Development Bank of Rwanda (BRD) Plc, the nation‚Äôs sole National Development Bank, plays a pivotal role in driving Rwanda‚Äôs Vision 2050. Over the past five years, the Bank has experienced remarkable growth, significantly contributing to Rwanda‚Äôs socio-economic transformation while enhancing institutional capacity, human capital, corporate governance, and risk management practices.

BRD is currently implementing its revised 2024‚Äì2028 strategic plan, designed in alignment with the country‚Äôs development priorities. This strategy positions the Bank to deliver greater value for its stakeholders by empowering entrepreneurs, addressing market inefficiencies, and accelerating impactful, inclusive economic growth.

To achieve its goals, BRD‚Äôs expanded mandate focuses on four strategic pillars:

  • Provision of transformational finance

  • Expansion of green financing for a resilient future

  • Driving scale and impact across sectors

  • Promoting innovation and technology

To fulfill this mandate, BRD is committed to building robust human and institutional capacity and maintaining excellence within Rwanda‚Äôs financial sector.

BRD strongly upholds gender equality and inclusion. Female candidates and persons with disabilities are especially encouraged to apply.

The Development Bank of Rwanda is seeking suitably qualified professionals to join its team in the following position:

OFFICER, GUARANTEE RISK (1 Position)

Background Information

Job Title: Officer, Guarantee Risk
Department: Credit Guarantee
Reports to: Manager, Credit Guarantee Risk
Contract Type: Open-Ended

Purpose of the Role

The Officer, Guarantee Risk, will support the risk management function of BRD‚Äôs Credit Guarantee instrument. The role involves implementing the Bank‚Äôs risk management framework through day-to-day risk assessment, analysis, reporting, monitoring, and control activities. This position is essential for managing and mitigating individual and portfolio-level credit risks associated with the Guarantee instrument, ensuring it effectively strengthens Rwanda‚Äôs MSME sector by expanding access to finance.

Key Responsibilities

  • Conduct due diligence and risk assessments for Participating Financial Institutions (PFIs) under the BRD Credit Guarantee.

  • Review risk profiles for guarantee applications, renewal requests, and rescheduling proposals in line with BRD‚Äôs guidelines.

  • Evaluate guarantee claim submissions and provide recommendations based on compliance with guarantee conditions.

  • Monitor Credit Guarantee portfolio performance, identify early warning signals, and follow up on high-risk exposures.

  • Maintain risk monitoring tools and ensure accurate and timely data entry into the MIS.

  • Carry out risk-based monitoring, including on-site and off-site assessments and periodic portfolio reviews.

  • Prepare risk reports and portfolio performance analyses to support management decisions.

  • Ensure adherence to internal risk policies, guarantee procedures, and regulatory requirements.

  • Propose improvements to the Credit Guarantee department‚Äôs risk tools, processes, and internal controls.

  • Perform any other duties assigned by line management or the Bank‚Äôs leadership.

Performance Indicators

Performance will be evaluated based on adherence to the Bank‚Äôs risk management framework and risk limits, the quality and accuracy of the Credit Guarantee portfolio, and the timeliness and effectiveness of the officer‚Äôs support to the Credit Guarantee Risk Manager and operations team, among other financial and operational metrics.

Qualifications, Skills, and Experience

  • Bachelor‚Äôs or master‚Äôs degree in finance, economics, business administration, or a related field.

  • Minimum of three years of experience in credit risk management, enterprise risk, portfolio analysis, or lending operations within a financial institution or guarantee scheme.

  • Strong expertise in credit assessment, portfolio monitoring, and early warning systems.

  • Up-to-date knowledge of the Rwandan banking environment, MSME financing landscape, and financial sector regulations.

  • Strong analytical and problem-solving skills to address credit-related challenges effectively.

  • Advanced financial modelling and Excel proficiency.

  • Strong people management capabilities.

  • Solid understanding of compliance, including KYC, AML, and CFT regulations (highly advantageous).

  • Experience delivering training, preparing credit manuals, and generating portfolio reports is desirable.

  • Excellent written and verbal communication skills with the ability to engage diverse stakeholders.

  • Ability to conduct precise analyses and ensure accuracy in credit assessments.

Application Guidelines

Interested applicants should submit their applications online via https://www.brd.rw/careers/.
Applications must include a Curriculum Vitae, copies of academic degrees and professional certificates, a motivation letter, and the names, emails, and phone numbers of three previous supervisors‚Äîall uploaded as a single document.

Only online applications will be accepted.

For inquiries (not applications), contact: recruitment@brd.rw

Address applications to:
Director, People, Culture and Corporate Services, BRD

Application Deadline: December 19, 2025

BRD offers a highly competitive and attractive employment package.
Only candidates meeting the required qualifications and experience will be shortlisted and contacted for interviews.

Issued in Kigali on Monday, December 9, 2025.

title: Relationship Officers at Umutanguha Finance Company Plc
description:
VACANCY ANNOUNCEMENT ‚Äì RELATIONSHIP OFFICERS

UMUTANGUHA Finance Company (UFC) Plc, a licensed Microfinance Institution operating under the National Bank of Rwanda, is seeking dynamic, self-driven, persuasive, and customer-focused individuals to join its team as Relationship Officers.
UFC Plc is registered under company code 101310843 and headquartered in Kigali, opposite Nyamirambo Pele Stadium, House #177, KN2 Avenue.
P.O. Box 2998 Kigali | Tel: 0788387730 | Email: info@ufinance.co.rw

We are looking for candidates with excellent communication, sales abilities, and strong client relationship skills to support our mission of providing high-quality financial services across Rwanda.

Key Responsibilities

A. Savings Mobilization

The Relationship Officer will drive deposit growth at the branch level by mobilizing savings and new accounts from both existing and potential clients. Key duties include:

  • Growing deposit volumes through customer acquisition and active field mobilization.

  • Promoting and selling UFC deposit products to current and prospective customers.

  • Building, strengthening, and maintaining long-term customer relationships through regular visits and engagement.

  • Identifying new business opportunities and cross-selling appropriate financial solutions.

  • Supporting savings promotional activities based on the branch‚Äôs operational needs.

  • Ensuring newly opened accounts are actively used by customers.

  • Managing the branch‚Äôs High-Net-Worth Individuals (HNWI) portfolio.

  • Meeting all business and deposit acquisition targets efficiently and on time.

B. Credit Responsibilities

The Relationship Officer is accountable for the quality and growth of the loan portfolio within the assigned branch. Duties include:

  • Mobilizing clients interested in accessing credit services.

  • Training individual clients and group members on UFC lending methodologies.

  • Supervising financial education sessions delivered by client trainers.

  • Monitoring client and group activities while offering guidance and support.

  • Conducting credit risk assessments through business and household visits to evaluate repayment capacity.

  • Preparing and submitting accurate loan documentation to facilitate disbursements.

  • Maintaining complete and updated loan records at the branch level.

  • Following up with borrowers to ensure timely repayment and loan recovery.

  • Participating in cluster meetings and implementing recovery actions for delinquent loans.

  • Preparing periodic reports on client numbers, repayments, PAR, recoveries, and follow-up actions.

C. Sales of Financial Products & Delivery Channels

  • Develop marketing and field plans to grow a reliable and active client base.

  • Identify, educate, and engage potential customers within the branch‚Äôs catchment area.

  • Sensitize clients on UFC Plc‚Äôs alternative delivery channels.

  • Refer eligible clients to other UFC departments for different financial products.

Performance Indicators

Performance will be evaluated based on:

  • Portfolio at Risk (PAR)

  • Value and growth of the outstanding loan portfolio

  • Number and growth of active loan clients

  • Growth in savings portfolio and number of saving customers

  • Strength and quality of client relationships

  • Customer service excellence

  • Compliance with Client Protection Principles

  • Upholding UFC Plc‚Äôs reputation

  • Fulfillment of any additional tasks assigned by the supervisor

Candidate Requirements

  • Bachelor‚Äôs degree in Economics, Management, Finance, Banking, or related fields.

  • Minimum of 2 years‚Äô experience in the banking or microfinance sector (preferably in Business or Credit operations).

  • Strong understanding of bank operations, lending processes, and credit analysis.

  • Excellent sales, negotiation, and analytical skills.

  • Strong communication skills (verbal and written).

  • Willingness and ability to work in any UFC branch across Rwanda.

  • A valid Category A driving license is an added advantage.

  • Maximum age: 40 years old.

Required Application Documents

(All documents must be scanned and submitted as one PDF file)

  • Application letter

  • Curriculum Vitae

  • Copy of National ID

  • Academic certificates and transcripts

  • Relevant training and experience certificates

  • Three professional references with their contact details

How to Apply

Submit your complete application electronically to:
üìß ufc.recruitment@ufinance.co.rw
Email subject: Relationship Officer

Application Deadline: 19th December 2025 at 5:00 PM

NB: Only shortlisted candidates will be contacted.

Mrs. Josephine MUKUNDIYIMANA

HR& Admin Manager


Mr. Noel MUHAWENIMANA

Chief Executive Officer

title: Laundry Attendant at Sambora Kinigi Lodge
description:
Job Title: Laundry Attendant

Location: Sambora Kinigi Lodge, Kinigi, Musanze, Rwanda 

Position Type: Full-Time 

About Sambora Kinigi Lodge: 

Sambora Kinigi Lodge is a renowned luxury lodge nestled in the scenic and serene landscapes of Kinigi, Musanze. Our lodge offers a unique and unforgettable experience to guests seeking a tranquil escape surrounded by the natural beauty of Rwanda. We are committed to providing exceptional service and maintaining the highest standards of cleanliness and comfort for our guests. 

Job Summary: 

The Housekeeper is responsible for maintaining the cleanliness and tidiness of guest rooms, public areas, and other lodge facilities. The successful candidate will play a critical role in ensuring that our guests enjoy a comfortable and welcoming environment during their stay. 

Key Responsibilities: 

Room Cleaning: Perform thorough cleaning of guest rooms and bathrooms, ensuring that all surfaces are sanitized and cleaned to the highest standards. 

Linen and Towel Care: Replace bed linens, towels, and amenities in guest rooms and ensure they are neatly arranged. 

Public Areas: Clean and maintain public areas, including the lobby, hallways, dining areas, and restrooms according to a schedule and ensure cleaning checklists are completed and signed. 

Inventory Management: Report any maintenance issues, damages, or shortages to the Housekeeping Supervisor or Management for timely resolution. 

Laundry Services: Manage and maintain a clean and efficient laundry area, including washing, ironing, and folding of linens and uniforms. 

Guest Requests: Attend promptly to guest requests for extra amenities, housekeeping services, and room refreshes. 

Waste Management: Properly dispose of waste and adhere to recycling practices. 

Team Collaboration: Work closely with other housekeeping staff to ensure that all areas are maintained to the highest standards. 

Compliance: Adhere to all company policies and procedures, including health and safety guidelines. 

Guest Interaction: Maintain a friendly and professional demeanour when interacting with guests, providing assistance and information as needed. 

Qualifications: 

  • High school diploma or equivalent. 

  • Previous experience in housekeeping, cleaning, or related roles is preferred.

  •  Attention to detail and a commitment to maintaining cleanliness and order.

  • Strong organizational and time-management skills. 

  • Ability to work effectively as part of a team.

  • Excellent communication and customer service skills. 

  • Flexibility to work shifts, including weekends and holidays. 

Physical Requirements: 

Ability to stand, walk, and perform physical tasks for extended periods. Lift and carry cleaning supplies and equipment. 

Bend, kneel, and reach to clean and maintain various areas. 

Tolerate exposure to cleaning chemicals and cleaning equipment. 

Benefits: 

Competitive salary. 

Employee meals during work hours 

Training and development opportunities. 

Friendly and supportive work environment. 

Healthcare insurance 

Sambora Kinigi Lodge is an equal opportunity employer. We encourage individuals from all backgrounds to apply for this position.

Performance Indicators

Key Performance Indicators (KPIs) for the Housekeeper role at Sambora Kinigi Lodge are essential to measure and evaluate the performance and effectiveness of the individual in this position. Here are some KPIs relevant to the Housekeeper role: 

Room Cleanliness and Quality: 

  • Percentage of Clean Rooms: The percentage of guest rooms inspected and deemed clean and ready for occupancy. 

  • Guest Satisfaction Score: Guest feedback and satisfaction ratings related to room cleanliness, including scores on post-stay surveys. 

Efficiency and Productivity: 

  • Rooms Cleaned Per Shift: The number of guest rooms cleaned during a typical shift, reflecting productivity. 

  • Response Time to Guest Requests: The time taken to fulfil guest requests for additional amenities or room refresh. 

Inventory and Resource Management: 

  •  Inventory Replenishment Accuracy: The accuracy of maintaining and replenishing guest room supplies, such as toiletries and linens. 

  • Laundry Efficiency: Measurement of laundry operations, including the number of linens processed per hour. 

Maintenance and Issue Reporting: 

  •  Maintenance Issue Reporting: Timeliness and accuracy of reporting maintenance issues or damages in guest rooms. 

  • Resolution Time: The time taken to address and resolve reported maintenance issues. Team Collaboration and Communication: 

  • Teamwork and Cooperation: Feedback from supervisors and colleagues on teamwork, cooperation, and communication skills. 

  • Communication with Guests: Feedback from guests on the housekeeper's professionalism and courtesy. 

Safety and Compliance: 

  •  Health and Safety Compliance: Adherence to safety guidelines and protocols, with a focus on preventing accidents and ensuring a safe work environment. 

  •  Adherence to Company Policies: Compliance with company policies and procedures, including housekeeping and cleanliness standards. 

Feedback and Improvement: 

  •  Self-Improvement: Participation in training and development opportunities to enhance housekeeping skills. 

  •  Feedback Implementation: Evidence of acting on feedback from supervisors or guest comments to improve performance.

Guest Interaction and Service: 

  • Positive Guest Interactions: The number of positive guest interactions, based on guest comments and feedback. 

  • Service Recovery: Handling and resolving guest complaints or issues effectively and in a manner that satisfies guests. 

Physical Maintenance: 

  •  Equipment Maintenance: Ensuring that cleaning equipment and tools are well-maintained and in good working condition. 

  • Uniform and Personal Hygiene: Maintaining personal hygiene and cleanliness while adhering to the uniform and appearance standards. 

Cost Control: 

  • Waste Reduction: Efforts to minimize waste and ensure efficient waste management practices. 

  • Supply Usage Efficiency: Efficient use of cleaning supplies, ensuring cost-effectiveness. 

These KPIs are designed to assess the housekeeper's performance in maintaining cleanliness, efficiency, and service quality.
Regularly tracking these indicators will help in maintaining high standards of housekeeping and guest satisfaction at
Sambora Kinigi Lodge.


Application: 

If you are a passionate culinary professional ready to contribute to Sambora Kinigi Lodge's commitment to excellence, we encourage you to apply. Please submit your resume and cover letter, detailing your experience and vision for the role. via this email careers@samborakinigi.com

Sambora Kinigi Lodge is an equal opportunity employer and embraces diversity in its team.

title: Pharmacists at Rwanda Medical Supply Ltd
description:
RMS Ltd JOB ADVERTISMENT

RMS Ltd is looking for qualified, dedicated & experienced individuals to fill the following positions:

PHARMACISTS: 8

Terms of Reference (TOR)

Background

Rwanda Medical Supply (RMS) Ltd faces recurring challenges in ensuring the timely availability of essential health commodities, including low order fill rates, long lead times, and communication delays between central and hospital levels. To address these gaps, RMS Ltd is deploying dedicated focal persons to selected referral hospitals. These individuals will strengthen collaboration, streamline communication, and provide on-site support to improve product availability and supply chain efficiency.

Objectives of the Role

The primary objective is to improve the availability and timely distribution of health commodities at large hospitals, through continuous on-site engagement. The role aims to:

  • Strengthen coordination between RMS Ltd and hospital stakeholders.

  • Ensure timely monitoring and follow-up of orders.

  • Reduce stock-outs, improve order fill rates, and shorten lead times.

  • Provide evidence-based feedback to inform RMS Ltd.‚Äôs decision-making.

Key Responsibilities

The person in this role will be responsible for the following:

Communication & Liaison

  • Act as the primary link between RMS Ltd and the hospital pharmacy/supply team.

  • Maintain effective communication with pharmacists, lab managers, clinicians, and hospital administration.

  • Monitor and support timely ordering through digital tools.

  • Participate in weekly meetings with hospital teams to review stock status, orders, and supply chain challenges.

  • Track deliveries and follow up on discrepancies or delays

  • Provide timely updates and recommendations to RMS Ltd HQ during product availability meetings.

Order & Stock Management

  • Monitor stock levels to prevent shortages and overstocks.

  • Facilitate timely submission and follow-up of hospital orders.

  • Track order status and escalating delays when necessary.

  • Maintain and regularly update a stock-out/priority needs list for RMS Ltd.

Data & System Support

  • Ensure hospital commodity lists are aligned with the National Product Catalogue (NPC).

  • Support accurate and timely data entry into RMS systems.

  • Provide routine reports on order trends, stock-outs, and fill rates.

Performance & Continuous Improvement

  • Identify bottlenecks in the supply chain and propose corrective actions.

  • Share lessons learned and best practices across hospitals and with RMS Ltd HQ.

  • Advise RMS Ltd on the identification of products that are frequently requested by referral hospitals, especially those facing recurrent supply challenges or stock out under partner scope and recommend their inclusion in the RMS Ltd product scope supported by evidence, to ensure uninterrupted service delivery at hospitals.

Required Skills & Qualifications

  • Bachelor‚Äôs degree in pharmacy (required); advanced training in supply chain management or public health is an asset.

  • Minimum of 1 years‚Äô experience in pharmacy, health supply chain, or clinical pharmacy.

  • Knowledge of Rwanda‚Äôs health supply chain and national product catalogue.

  • Proficiency in data management and reporting tools.

  • High degree of initiative, problem-solving, and accountability.

  • Strong communication, analytical, and coordination skills.

  • Previous experience in hospital pharmacy or public health supply chain is an asset.

Reporting & Coordination

  • The hospital-based focal person will report to the designated Supply Warehouse, Sales, Marketing and Distribution Department at RMS Ltd.

  • They will collaborate closely with RMS Central Warehouse focal persons.

  • Deliverables will include:

  • Weekly hospital supply chain updates.

  • Monthly performance reports (stock-outs, order fill rate, lead time trends).

  • Action plans to address identified challenges.

Duration:

Initial appointment is for 12 Months, renewable based on performance and program needs.

Job application procedure:

Interested candidates should send their application documents (in one PDF document) including application letter, Curriculum Vitae, copy of ID, copies of degree certificates and professional certificates, motivation letter, names of three referees as well as their emails and telephones.

All applications are to be addressed to the Chief Executive Officer of Rwanda Medical Supply Ltd through the following email address: recruitment@rms.rw

Deadline for application: Monday, 22 /12/2025 at 5:00 pm.

N.B:

  1. Only complete applications sent via the above e-mail shall be considered. 

  2. Only Candidates with the right qualifications and relevant experience shall be shortlisted and contacted.

title: Technical Training Manager at RwandAir Ltd
description:
Technical Training Manager ‚Äì RwandAir Ltd

Location: Kigali International Airport, Rwanda
Department: Technical Services (Maintenance)
Reports To: Director, Technical Services
Job Type: Full-time
Deadline: 12 January 2026

Job Overview

RwandAir Ltd, the national flag carrier airline of Rwanda, operates domestic and international services across Africa, Europe, and the Middle East from its hub at Kigali International Airport. As part of its growth and transformation strategy, RwandAir is seeking a highly qualified Technical Training Manager to lead and manage the airline‚Äôs technical training and apprenticeship programs.

The role is critical in ensuring regulatory compliance, workforce competence, and the continuous development of technical talent to support aircraft maintenance and airworthiness operations.

Key Responsibilities

Operational Responsibilities

  • Develop and manage the maintenance apprenticeship program to ensure a sustainable pipeline of technical talent.

  • Design, develop, and administer technical training courses and materials in line with approved standards.

  • Develop and coordinate annual and recurrent training plans in collaboration with Technical section heads.

  • Review and approve all technical training requests, ensuring staff meet course prerequisites.

  • Maintain confidential examination banks and administer assessments in accordance with approved procedures.

  • Identify and outsource specialized technical training where in-house capability is unavailable.

  • Develop, update, and manage all Technical Training procedures in coordination with Compliance and Safety.

  • Support on-the-job training (OJT) and practical training requirements.

  • Maintain training facilities, classrooms, and equipment.

  • Compile and manage the Technical Training budget.

  • Maintain accurate and up-to-date training records for all Technical staff.

  • Conduct recurrent and mandatory regulatory training as required by aviation authorities.

  • Monitor regulatory, procedural, and operational changes and integrate them into training programs.

  • Ensure confidentiality and security of training materials, records, and examination results.

  • Participate in assessment panels for maintenance and airworthiness staff authorization and renewals when required.

  • Ensure Safety Management System (SMS) compliance within the training function.

  • Train, mentor, and assess the competence of Technical Training staff.

Strategic Responsibilities

  • Forecast long-term technical training requirements to ensure continued regulatory compliance.

  • Monitor trends in aircraft maintenance and airworthiness and align training accordingly.

  • Identify and implement strategically and financially beneficial training programs for the airline.

Stakeholder Management

  • Liaise with Technical department heads and HR Talent Development teams.

  • Coordinate development of training materials with relevant technical sections.

Leadership & Management

  • Lead and manage a team of Technical Instructors.

  • Develop instructor competencies aligned with fleet complexity and regulatory changes.

  • Promote a safety-focused, high-accountability culture.

  • Support mentoring and professional development, particularly for national staff.

Qualifications & Experience

Essential

  • Bachelor‚Äôs degree in Aeronautical Engineering or a related technical discipline,
    OR Licensed Aircraft Engineer (EASA Part 66 or ICAO Type II) with relevant aircraft type endorsements and a minimum of 8 years‚Äô experience.

  • At least 8 years of experience in Technical Training, including 3 years in a leadership or management role.

  • Strong knowledge of aviation regulations (Part 145, CAMO, Part 66, Part 147).

  • Strong understanding of aircraft maintenance processes, certification procedures, and training organization requirements.

  • Knowledge of Safety Management Systems (SMS).

Preferred

  • Experience in airline or MRO technical training environments.

  • Familiarity with maintenance systems such as AMOS or TRAX.

  • Knowledge of aircraft types operated by RwandAir.

Skills & Personal Attributes

  • Strong communication and coordination skills across multiple stakeholders.

  • Knowledge of EASA and RCAA regulatory frameworks.

  • High attention to detail and strong organizational skills.

  • Fluency in English (French or Kinyarwanda is an added advantage).

  • Strong aeronautical and airline technical background.

  • Ability to plan, prioritize, and manage multiple tasks effectively.

  • Proven leadership, mentoring, coaching, and team development skills.

How to Apply

Interested candidates should submit the following documents in PDF format only:

  • Application letter addressed to the Chief HR & Administration Officer

  • Recent Curriculum Vitae (CV)

  • Notarized copies of degree/diploma certificates

  • Relevant professional certificates

  • Copies of academic papers

  • Copy of Passport or National ID

  • Contact details of three referees

üîó Apply Here: https://erecruitment.rwandair.com/Home/Moreinfo/RN000276
‚è∞ Application Deadline: 12 January 2026

title: Early Childhood Development (ECD) Program Officer at Better World (BW)
description:
JOB VACANCY ANNOUNCEMENT

Position Title: Early Childhood Development (ECD) Program Officer

Department: ECD Program
Reports To: Country Director
Duty Station: Rwamagana District, Rwanda
Employment Type: Full-Time

About Better World Rwanda

Better World (BW) is an international non-governmental organization originating from South Korea, committed to sustainable, people-centered community development. In Rwanda, Better World operates as Better World Rwanda (BWR), based in Rwamagana District.

BWR implements integrated development programs in education, agriculture, health, livelihoods, and women‚Äôs empowerment, working closely with local communities, government institutions, and international partners. Guided by the values of compassion, integrity, and collaboration, Better World Rwanda contributes to building resilient and self-reliant communities aligned with Rwanda‚Äôs national development priorities.

To strengthen its Early Childhood Development initiatives, Better World Rwanda is seeking a qualified and motivated ECD Program Officer.

Position Overview

The ECD Program Officer will be responsible for supporting the design, implementation, monitoring, and quality assurance of Early Childhood Development (ECD) interventions in Rwamagana District. The role focuses on improving service delivery, strengthening caregiver capacity, enhancing school readiness, and ensuring alignment with national ECD guidelines.

Key Responsibilities

  • Monitor ECD program activities to track progress, quality, and effective resource utilization.

  • Assess the quality of ECD services in line with national ECD standards and guidelines.

  • Ensure ECD centers implement the approved ECD curriculum effectively.

  • Provide continuous coaching and mentoring support to caregivers to improve service quality.

  • Facilitate school readiness activities across all supported ECD centers.

  • Support smooth transition of children from ECD centers to formal primary education.

  • Establish and maintain strong partnerships with government institutions and ECD stakeholders in the district.

  • Collect, analyze, and report essential program data to support decision-making.

  • Support the establishment and use of community-managed information management systems.

  • Monitor child development and facilitate referrals to specialized services when required.

  • Promote community resource mobilization to sustain ECD services and motivate caregivers.

  • Support caregivers in developing daily lesson plans and play-based learning activities.

  • Perform any other duties assigned by the supervisor.

Required Qualifications & Experience

  • Bachelor‚Äôs degree in Early Childhood Development, Nursery Education, or Education.

  • Minimum 3 years of teaching experience at lower primary level.

  • At least 2 years of experience working with an NGO in direct project implementation.

  • Minimum 3 years of experience in ECD programming.

  • Specialized training in Early Childhood Education is an added advantage.

  • Strong knowledge of play-based learning methodologies.

  • Experience in mentoring or peer coaching.

  • Proven experience in project monitoring, data collection, and reporting.

  • Proficiency in Microsoft Office applications.

  • Fluency in English and Kinyarwanda.

Skills and Competencies

  • Strong pedagogical expertise in early childhood education.

  • Leadership and team motivation skills.

  • Excellent interpersonal and stakeholder engagement abilities.

  • Data collection, entry, and basic analysis skills.

  • Ability to apply child-centered and play-based teaching methodologies.

  • Strong mentoring and coaching capabilities.

  • Excellent written and verbal communication skills.

  • Ability to provide constructive and supportive feedback.

How to Apply

Interested candidates should submit the following documents in English:

  • Application letter

  • Updated Curriculum Vitae (CV)

  • Names and contacts of three (3) professional referees

üìß Application Email: info.betterworldrwanda@gmail.com
üóì Application Deadline: 9 January 2025

title: GRAPHIC DESIGN ANALYST at  African Institute for Mathematical Sciences (AIMS)
description:
JOB OPPORTUNITY: GRAPHIC DESIGN ANALYST

Organization: African Institute for Mathematical Sciences (AIMS)
Location: Kigali, Rwanda
Contract Type: One-year, Full-Time
Reporting To: Communications Manager, Mastercard Foundation Scholars Program
Application Deadline: January 15, 2026

About AIMS

The African Institute for Mathematical Sciences (AIMS) is a pan-African network of centres of excellence dedicated to postgraduate training, research, and public engagement in mathematical sciences and STEM. Founded in 2003 in Cape Town, South Africa, AIMS has since expanded to Senegal, Ghana, Cameroon, and two centres in Rwanda.

AIMS empowers talented young Africans to become creative leaders in science, technology, academia, government, and industry through world-class education delivered by leading international lecturers in an intensive learning environment.

Position Overview

Based at the AIMS Research and Innovation Centre (AIMS RIC), the Graphic Design Analyst will support institutional programs by creating high-quality visual content, including graphic designs, motion graphics, and video edits. The role requires both creative design skills and an understanding of effective visual communication.

Key Responsibilities

  • Design visually engaging content such as graphics, illustrations, motion graphics, and edited videos

  • Develop communication materials for various platforms, including social media, events, and promotional campaigns

  • Collaborate with program and communications teams to understand objectives and translate them into compelling visual assets

  • Support multiple departments while ensuring brand consistency and high-quality output

  • Assist in producing event banners, digital publications, and other design materials

  • Coordinate with the Communications Manager to manage timelines and meet deadlines

  • Contribute creative ideas to enhance visual storytelling and communication strategies

  • Maintain and organize the digital asset library for easy access and reuse

Required Qualifications and Experience

  • Recently completed a degree in Communication, Graphic Design, or a related field

  • Proficiency in Canva and Adobe Creative Suite (Illustrator, Photoshop, Premiere Pro, After Effects)

  • Strong understanding of design principles, typography, and visual storytelling

  • Experience translating communication concepts into engaging visual content

  • Familiarity with video editing tools and techniques

  • A portfolio showcasing graphic design and motion graphics work

  • Excellent communication and collaboration skills

  • Strong organizational skills, attention to detail, and ability to meet deadlines

  • Commitment to the mission and values of AIMS

How to Apply

Interested candidates should submit:

  • A letter of motivation, including salary expectations

  • A detailed Curriculum Vitae (CV)

üìß Send applications to: application@aimsric.org
üìå Email subject line: Graphic Design Analyst

Deadline: January 15, 2026

Applicants who do not receive feedback within five weeks after the deadline should consider their application unsuccessful. AIMS RIC reserves the right not to make an appointment.

Equal Opportunity Statement

AIMS RIC is an equal opportunity employer and is committed to diversity and inclusion.

title: Call for Applications: Youth Leadership Program_2026-2027(Digital Champions & Business Coaches ) at  Digital Opportunity Trust (DOT) Rwanda
description:
Call for Applications: Youth Leadership Program 2026-2027

Location: Community-Based
Application Deadline: Wednesday, 21st January 2026, 05:00 PM GMT+2

Are you a passionate young leader committed to community empowerment and digital inclusion?

Join the movement! Digital Opportunity Trust (DOT) Rwanda, under the Digital Skills for Employability (DSE) program, in partnership with the Mastercard Foundation, is now accepting applications for the Youth Leadership Program 2026-2027.

About the Digital Skills for Employability (DSE) Program

The DSE program is a four-year transformative initiative contributing to Rwanda‚Äôs National Strategy for Transformation (NST2) 2024‚Äì2029, Vision 2050, and the Mastercard Foundation‚Äôs Young Africa Works strategy.

Implemented by a consortium led by DOT Rwanda, in partnership with Intango Technical Secondary School (TSS), Igire Rwanda Organization (IRO), Knowledge LAB (kLab), and SOLVIT Africa, the program empowers over 10,000 young people‚Äîespecially young women, rural youth, persons with disabilities, and refugees‚Äîby providing digital and entrepreneurial skills needed to thrive in Rwanda‚Äôs digital economy.

Through Beginner Digital and Business Skills, participants gain:

  • Fundamental digital literacy

  • Entrepreneurship training

  • Skills in financial management and marketing

  • Personalized coaching, mentorship, and access to finance

  • Supportive business networks

The program prioritizes youth who are not in education or employment, particularly in rural areas, with a focus on empowering young women.

Why Join the Youth Leadership Program?

As a Digital Champion and Business Coach, you will:

  • Gain digital skills and social impact expertise

  • Boost your agency and access new work opportunities

  • Deliver Digital Skills for Business training in your local community

  • Empower micro, small, and informal business owners with training in digital tools, entrepreneurship, financial management, and marketing

Program Benefits:

  • Comprehensive Training: Leadership, digital, and entrepreneurial skills, plus career development and employment linkages

  • Become a Coach and Changemaker: Serve as a role model and mentor to peers

  • Empower Your Community: Support local MSMEs in business growth and digital adoption

  • Join the #DOTYouth Community: Connect with a vibrant network of young leaders across Rwanda

Eligibility Criteria

Applicants must:

  • Be university/college graduates aged 21‚Äì35, or secondary school graduates aged 21‚Äì35 with at least two years of community engagement

  • Be currently not in education, employment, or training (NEET)

  • Have basic online collaboration skills (e.g., Google Drive, Zoom)

  • Be proficient in written and spoken English and Kinyarwanda

  • Have a passion for community empowerment, digital inclusion, and gender equality

  • Be residents of and committed to working in one of the following districts for one year: City of Kigali: Gasabo, Kicukiro, Nyarugenge
    Southern Province: Gisagara, Muhanga, Nyamagabe, Ruhango, Nyanza
    Eastern Province: Bugesera, Gatsibo, Nyagatare, Kirehe, Ngoma
    Northern Province: Burera, Gakenke, Musanze, Rulindo
    Western Province: Karongi, Rutsiro, Nyamasheke, Rubavu

This is a community-based role, requiring work directly in the selected district. Apply only if willing and able to work in that location.

We strongly encourage applications from:

  • Young women

  • Youth with disabilities

  • Refugees

DOT Rwanda alumni from previous internship programs are not eligible.
Non-graduates, current students, and full-time employees will not be considered.

How to Apply

Submit your application by clicking on "APPLY BUTTON at the bottom of the page"

Note: A Gmail account is required to view and upload documents.

DOT Rwanda celebrates diversity and ensures an inclusive environment. Reasonable accommodations are available for individuals with disabilities‚Äîplease indicate any needs in your application.

title: Legal Intern & Lawyer at Hengtian Attorneys Rwanda Ltd
description:
Job Title: Legal Intern & Lawyer

Organization: Hengtian Attorneys
Location: Rwanda
Employment Type: Full-time

Position Overview

Hengtian Attorneys is a law firm providing high-quality legal services to Chinese-invested companies operating in Rwanda. We are seeking a motivated and detail-oriented Legal Intern & Lawyer to support our legal team in delivering professional, reliable, and compliant legal services.

This role is ideal for candidates who are passionate about legal practice and eager to gain hands-on experience in Rwandan corporate law, investment advisory, regulatory compliance, immigration matters, and litigation support.

Key Responsibilities

1. Investment & Corporate Advisory (FDI Support)

  • Assist in providing legal guidance on Foreign Direct Investment (FDI) procedures in Rwanda, from company setup to full investment implementation.

  • Support senior counsel in advising clients on obtaining Investment Registration Certificates (IRC) and company registration through the Rwanda Development Board (RDB).

  • Prepare and submit documents for company incorporation, business restructuring, and social security registration (RSSB).

2. Regulatory Compliance & Government Liaison

  • Conduct legal research and assist in advisory services related to:

    • Law Governing Companies

    • Investment Promotion Law

    • Tax Law

    • Labor Law

    • Real Estate Law

    • Civil Code and relevant Ministerial Orders and Regulations

  • Liaise with government institutions such as RDB, Rwanda Revenue Authority (RRA), and other relevant authorities to follow up on client applications and resolve administrative matters.

  • Support statutory filings and ensure full compliance with current Rwandan laws and regulations.

  • Draft legal opinions on labor disputes, contract drafting and review, land law, and related matters.

3. Immigration & Expatriate Services

  • Assist with applications for Investment Visas, Work Permits, and Temporary Resident Permits (TRPs) through the Directorate General of Immigration and Emigration (DGIE).

  • Advise foreign clients on legal requirements related to expatriate employment and residency under Rwandan law.

4. Legal Research, Drafting & Analysis

  • Conduct comprehensive legal research and draft legal memoranda, briefs, and opinions.

  • Draft and review commercial contracts and agreements under the supervision of senior lawyers.

  • Participate in client consultations and legal briefings on regulatory updates, new laws, or judicial decisions affecting business operations.

5. Litigation Support & Court Attendance

  • Assist in drafting court documents, including pleadings, summons, affidavits, and submissions for the Commercial Court, High Court, and Intermediate Courts.

  • Attend court hearings with senior advocates, take detailed notes, and assist in managing case files and evidence.

6. Administrative Support

  • Perform administrative and operational tasks as assigned by the supervisor in support of legal service delivery.

Requirements & Qualifications

  • Education: Bachelor of Laws (LLB) from a recognized university.

  • Professional Status: Licensed advocate is an advantage.

  • Technical Skills: Experience with IECMS (Integrated Electronic Case Management System) is a strong advantage.

  • Language Skills: Full professional proficiency in English and Kinyarwanda.

  • High ethical standards, integrity, and strong attention to detail.

  • Excellent interpersonal and communication skills.

  • Ability to work independently, manage deadlines, and handle multiple assignments effectively.

How to Apply

title: Accountant Secretary at COMBINAISON Ltd
description:
JOB DESCRIPTION

COMBINAISON Ltd established in 2014. We are top leading supplier of a wide range of laboratoryproducts for a variety of sectors, including medical, agriculture veterinary and forensic science. From public institutions to large private corporates, we are committed to providing you with high-qualityproducts from trusted manufacturers and we strive to ensure that you get the equipment and suppliesyou need to conduct your work with confidence.

For more than 10 years, COMBINAISON Ltd has built a solid reputation for its self and is constantly expanding with a good corporate image and we have the ability to satisfy the ever-changing, more recent needs of our clients around Rwanda. We actively work together with various manufacturers and suppliers for the supply of genuine solutions in order to meet the growing demand for superior laboratory products.

  • JOB TITLE: Accountant Secretary

  • RERORT TO: Operations Manager 

SCOPE OF THE JOB

The Accountant Secretary is responsible for supporting the day-to-day operations of the Finance Department by performing entry-level accounting tasks.

 The primary focus of this role is maintaining accurate records related to accounts payable and ensuring timely reconciliation. The role also involves assisting with tax computations and tax declarations, contributing to the overall accuracy and compliance of financial operations.

Key Responsibilities

Accounting Duties

  1. Preparation of financial and statistical reports.

  2. Analyze financial data to identify and resolve discrepancies.

  3. Apply relevant accounting policies, standards, and regulations to ensure compliance.

  4. Compile and prepare routine financial reports and summaries.

  5. Perform any other reasonable tasks assigned by the managing director

  6. Maintain the confidentiality and integrity of all Company financial data.

  7. Maintain accurate and up-to-date financial records

  8. Maintain accurate and up-to-date financial records.

  9. Prepare and file daily financial transactions (invoices, receipts, payments).

  10. Manage accounts payable and accounts receivable.

  11. Prepare bank reconciliations and follow up on outstanding balances.

  12. Assist in preparing monthly, quarterly, and annual financial reports.

  13. Support the preparation of tax declarations in compliance with Rwanda Revenue Authority (RRA).

  14. Manage petty cash and prepare expense summaries.

  15. Ensure proper filing and storage of all accounting documents.

ADMINISTRATIVE & SECRETARIAL DUTIES

  1. Manage front-office operations: receive visitors, answer calls, and respond to emails.

  2. Maintain company records, correspondence, and filing systems (both physical and digital).

  3. Draft and format official letters and reports.

  4. Schedule appointments, meetings, and assist in planning company activities.

  5. Prepare meeting minutes and follow up on action points.

  6. Coordinate with suppliers, clients, and internal teams for smooth workflow.

  7. Support procurement processes by preparing purchase orders when needed.

  8. Maintain inventory documents related to office and administrative supplies.

KNOWLEDGE AND SKILLS

Minimum Education and Qualification Required (Added advantage)

  1. Bachelor‚Äôs degree in accounting or related field

  2. Completed at least intermediate level /part two of CPA or ACCA

  3. Having excellent relevant knowledge in tax matters

  4. Excellent degree of accuracy and attention to detail

  5. Excellent computer literacy with high proficiency in Microsoft Excel(advanced)

  6. Excellent interpersonal skills

  7. Result - driven with a strong capacity to work autonomously

  8. Compliance oriented and auditing skills

  9. Professional Etiquette and Integrity

  10. Fluency in English and Kinyarwanda

Applications must include the following documents:

  • Application cover letter addressed to the company Managing Director

  • Stating where you heard about the position and why you should be considered

  • Curriculum vitae (CV) including your personal details, education level, and any experience 

  • Name, address, and telephone numbers of three (3) personal references

  • Copy of ID card or Passport

  • Passport photo

  • Copy of Bachelor‚Äôs Degree

The required documents should be submitted in scanned soft copies in PDF format (preferably as one document) to info@combinaisonltd.com and to combinaisonltd@gmail.com.

title: Assistant to the General Production Manager at HAARZOPF Ltd
description:
Assistant to the General Production Manager 

About us

Our hair factory is a dynamically growing production company that manufactures high-quality hair products for international markets. To support our Production Manager, we are looking for a committed, reliable and structured individual who combines organizational skills with practical implementation strength.

Your responsibilities

As Assistant to the Production Manager, you will act as the central interface between production, administration, human resources, import/export, accounting and warehousing. You will ensure that all administrative and logistical processes in the factory run efficiently, transparently and smoothly.
1. Human resources 

a) Search for employees

b) draft Job descriptions advertisings and let it approve

c) Publishing and deleting job advertisements

d) manage candidate data and CV¬¥s in Bitrix24

Scheduling interviews and, if necessary,

conducting interviews with candidates according to the Companies HR Matrix and HR manual

e) Maintaining and managing personnel files

f) Drafting employment contracts, contract extensions and terminations

g) Recording working hours and assisting with payroll accounting

h) Organizing training courses, safety briefings and further education

i) Acting as a point of contact for employees in general personnel matters


2. Import management

  1. Preparation, control and management of all import documents, customs documents, certificates of origin, required company licenses, and all relevant documents 

  2. Communication with suppliers, freight forwarders and authorities, and customs, RRA, RICA, FDA

  3. Handling of all formalities, completion of all clearance procedures for imports in compliance with all relevant RWANDA regulations and systems 

  4. Monitoring deadlines and tracking goods deliveries

  5. Checking delivery notes, invoices and goods receipts in our MUB warehouse, up to correct entry in our stock control system

3. Export management

  1. Preparation, control and management of all export documents, customs documents and certificates of origin, and all other required docs like NON-COMMERCIAL INVOICE, PACKING LIST, stock control system, Airway Bills, Bill of Lading etc.

  2. Communication with suppliers, carriers and all RWANDA authorities

  3. Handling of all formalities, completion of all customs clearance procedures for exports in compliance with all relevant customs regulations and systems 

  4. Monitoring of payment from the customers, the deadlines and tracking of goods from deliveries

  5. Checking delivery notes, invoices and goods leaving our MUB warehouse with correct entry in our stock control system

  6. Coordination with carriers and international customers

  7. Monitoring shipping dates and export regulations

  8. Maintaining customer data and documenting export processes

4. Warehouse management and stock control system

  1. As long as there is no in-house stock manager in the company to take on the following tasks, you will be responsible for performing all of the following tasks accurately and perfectly. You will then be responsible for training the new stock manager and monitoring their bookings, work and inventories.

  2. Booking incoming materials and maintaining stock levels, MUB stock and local stock levels in our stock control system.

  3. Monitoring material movements and write-offs

  4. Regular stock checks and preparation of inventory, reporting daily and weekly

  5. Supporting the optimization of warehouse processes

  6. Preparing warehouse statistics and consumption analyses and submitting them to the customs and tax authorities and reconciling the data with these authorities.
    YOU ARE RESPONSIBLE FOR ENSURING THAT THE COMPANY DOES NOT ENCOUNTER ANY DIFFICULTIES WITH THE AUTHORITIES and does not have to pay any penalties.

5. Administrative management of the factory

a. Organization and maintenance of all administrative processes in the office and in various software programs: Bitrix24, Office 365, ZOHO, Excel Stock control system, training materials, accounting, Excel reports, folder creation and management, data storage, contract creation, etc.

b. Management of contracts, maintenance and service agreements

c. Support in executing cost control, and delivering the reports

d. Scheduling and video and live meetings for the production manager, coordination of internal and external meetings, including minute-taking

6. Accounting

a. As long as there are no junior accountants in the company, and you take on the following tasks, you must perform all of the following tasks accurately and perfectly. Afterwards, train new junior accountants and monitor their bookings, work and activities.

b. Accounting: daily accounting tasks, including recording business transactions and managing accounts and petty cash, expenses, imports, exports, payroll accounting, wages and salaries, and all taxes and duties.

c. Invoice processing: creating outgoing invoices, checking and processing incoming invoices, and monitoring and posting incoming payments.

d. Accounts payable and accounts receivable: managing the relevant accounts and associated processes for debtors and creditors.

e. Closing and closing procedures: assisting with the preparation of monthly and annual financial statements and the preparation and submission of tax returns and VAT returns.

f. Data maintenance and reporting: Maintenance and archiving of receipts and accounting documents, as well as preparation of analyses and statistics.

g. Communication: Correspondence with internal and external partners such as suppliers and banks.

h. Process optimization: Contributing to the continuous development and improvement of accounting processes.

Your profile

  • EXCELLENT EXCEL SKILLS (if required, we will provide excel trainings for you)

  • Completed commercial training (e.g. industrial clerk, freight forwarding clerk, office clerk) or comparable qualification as bachelor

  • Professional experience in a manufacturing company, ideally in the textile industry

  • Knowledge of import/export and customs clearance is an advantage

  • Perfect application of MS Office (Excel, Word, Outlook) and ERP/warehouse management systems

  • Good written and spoken English

  • Structured, independent and responsible way of working

  • Organizational skills, strong communication skills and team spirit

  • Resilience and flexibility in a dynamic environment, ready for overtime

We offer

  • A varied and responsible position with development potential

  • Close cooperation with production management and senior management

  • A collegial and appreciative working environment

  • Modern work equipment and structured training

  • Long-term prospects in a growing company

  • Attractive salary. Milestone Bonus system: 6 Milestone per Year 

  • Meal supply

  • Probation period 3 Month 

Reporting line

Direct supervisor: Production manager and managing director of the company 

Close cooperation with: Management, Human Resources, Accounting, Warehouse Management, Shipping Companies, Suppliers and Customers

title: IT Officer at King Faisal Hospital Rwanda Foundation (KFHRF)
description:
Job Description: IT Officer

Secondment Institution: Africa Health Sciences University (AHSU)
Duty Station: Kigali, Rwanda (with regular travel to clinical teaching sites nationwide)
Contract Type: Full-Time

Position Overview

Africa Health Sciences University (AHSU) is seeking a highly motivated and skilled IT Officer to support the design, implementation, and ongoing management of its information and communication technology (ICT) systems. This role is central to strengthening AHSU‚Äôs digital infrastructure across academic, administrative, and clinical training environments.

The IT Officer will play a key role in supporting digital learning platforms, ensuring secure and reliable connectivity at teaching sites, and providing responsive technical support to faculty, residents, and students. Working closely with university leadership and partner hospitals, the role contributes to building modern, secure, and scalable technology systems that enable excellence in education, research, and institutional operations.

Key Responsibilities

A. ICT Infrastructure Development & Maintenance

  • Design, deploy, and maintain ICT infrastructure, including networks, servers, firewalls, connectivity, and backup systems.

  • Conduct ICT needs assessments for new offices, classrooms, simulation centers, and clinical teaching sites.

  • Develop and implement ICT policies, standard operating procedures, and maintenance plans.

  • Supervise installation and configuration of routers, switches, cabling, and related hardware to ensure system stability and security.

B. Academic & Digital Learning Support

  • Teach Digital Health and other IT-related modules to undergraduate and postgraduate students, as well as faculty members.

  • Support the setup, administration, and troubleshooting of learning management systems (LMS), student portals, and digital examination platforms.

  • Provide technical support for virtual teaching, surgical tele-education tools (e.g., Proximie), simulation-based learning, and online assessments.

  • Ensure digital readiness and connectivity for residency and midwifery rotations across partner hospitals.

C. User Support & Service Delivery

  • Deliver timely and effective IT support to staff, faculty, residents, and students.

  • Conduct training sessions on digital platforms, tools, and cybersecurity best practices.

  • Troubleshoot hardware, software, audiovisual equipment, and digital classroom systems.

D. Data Security & Compliance

  • Implement cybersecurity measures to ensure secure access to academic and administrative systems.

  • Protect sensitive data, including student records, institutional documents, and research materials, in line with data protection standards.

E. Hardware & Software Management

title: Officer, Guarantee Operations at Development Bank of Rwanda (BRD)
description:
VACANCY ANNOUNCEMENT

The Development Bank of Rwanda (BRD) Plc, the country‚Äôs sole National Development Bank, plays a central role in advancing Rwanda‚Äôs Vision 2050. Over the last five years, BRD has achieved exceptional growth, contributing significantly to national socio-economic progress, strengthening institutional and human capacity, and enhancing corporate governance and risk management systems.

BRD is currently implementing its revised 2024‚Äì2028 strategic plan, which is aligned with the nation‚Äôs long-term development ambitions. This strategy is designed to unlock greater value for stakeholders by supporting entrepreneurship, addressing market gaps, and driving impactful socio-economic transformation.

To fulfill its ambitious mandate, the Bank‚Äôs expanded focus is structured around four strategic pillars:

  • Delivering transformational finance

  • Scaling up green financing for a resilient future

  • Driving sector-wide scale and impact

  • Advancing innovation and technology

As part of its commitment to excellence, BRD continues to invest in strong human and institutional capacity to ensure it remains a leading development finance institution in the region.

BRD promotes gender equality and disability inclusion. Female applicants and persons with disabilities are strongly encouraged to apply.

To support its mission, BRD is seeking qualified and motivated professionals for the following role:

OFFICER, GUARANTEE OPERATIONS (3 Positions)

Background Information

Job Title: Credit Guarantee Facility Operations Officer
Department: Credit Guarantee
Reports to: Manager, Guarantee Operations
Contract Type: Open-Ended

Purpose of the Role

The Credit Guarantee Operations Officer is responsible for increasing the uptake and utilization of BRD‚Äôs Credit Guarantee Facility among Participating Financial Institutions (PFIs), including commercial banks, MFIs, and SACCOs. The role focuses on proactive engagement, capacity building, and continuous support to ensure seamless onboarding, proper usage, and effective performance of guarantee products.

Key responsibilities include conducting due diligence, managing guarantee issuance, monitoring portfolio performance, processing claims, and ensuring operational compliance with BRD policies and the Credit Guarantee Facility‚Äôs guidelines. This position plays a vital role in strengthening BRD‚Äôs Credit Guarantee operations and building strong, sustainable partnerships with PFIs.

Key Responsibilities

  • Identify, engage, and onboard eligible PFIs into the Credit Guarantee Facility.

  • Conduct operational due diligence on PFIs to assess compliance with Credit Guarantee Facility procedures.

  • Coordinate the signing and renewal of Guarantee Framework Agreements (GFAs) and support PFIs in understanding eligibility criteria, operational requirements, and claims procedures.

  • Ensure accurate and updated documentation and records within the Credit Guarantee management system.

  • Prepare guarantee issuance requests, ensuring all documentation is complete and compliant.

  • Maintain ongoing communication with PFIs to collect operational reports, monitor adherence to guarantee terms, and provide necessary support.

  • Process guarantee claims by validating documentation and ensuring compliance with claims procedures.

  • Assist in developing and updating operational procedures, guidelines, and training materials to improve efficiency and promote best practices.

  • Provide operational assistance to ensure effective implementation of the Credit Guarantee Facility.

  • Prepare operational reports to support management and Credit Guarantee Committee decision-making.

  • Ensure PFIs submit timely, complete, and accurate periodic reports.

  • Support routine portfolio monitoring activities and audits of the Credit Guarantee Facility.

  • Build and manage relationships with PFIs to meet their risk-sharing needs and maximize guarantee utilization.

  • Maintain strong market intelligence to inform strategic and operational decisions for the Credit Guarantee Project.

  • Perform other duties as required by the department or Bank leadership.

Performance Indicators

Performance will be assessed based on business volume, revenue generated through Credit Guarantee operations, PFI satisfaction (including adherence to turnaround times and survey results), and additional financial performance metrics.

Qualifications, Skills & Experience

  • A bachelor‚Äôs or master‚Äôs degree in finance, economics, business administration, or a related discipline.

  • At least three years of progressive experience within Rwanda‚Äôs financial services sector.

  • Strong and current understanding of the Rwandan banking sector, MSME financing landscape, and relevant financial regulations.

  • Demonstrated strong analytical, organizational, and relationship management capabilities.

  • Strong financial analysis skills.

  • Excellent written and verbal communication skills with the ability to engage diverse stakeholders effectively.

  • Solid understanding of credit processes, risk mitigation practices, and financial institution operations.

Application Guidelines

Interested applicants should submit their applications online at https://www.brd.rw/careers/ and upload the following documents as one combined file:

  • Curriculum Vitae

  • Copies of academic and professional certificates

  • Motivation letter

  • Names, emails, and telephone contacts of three previous supervisors

Only online applications will be accepted.

Director, People, Culture and Corporate Services, BRD

title: Internal Auditor at RULI HIGHER INSTITUTE OF HEALTH
description:
JOB DESCRIPTION

Job Profile: Internal Auditor

Organization: Ruli Higher Institute of Health (RHIH)
Department: Office of the Vice Chancellor
Job Title: Internal Auditor
Job Level & Type: Level 3 ‚Äì Full-Time
Reports to: Vice Chancellor / Audit Committee of the Governing Body
Location: RHIH Headquarters, Ruli Sector, Gakenke District, Northern Province

1. Job Summary

The Internal Auditor provides independent, objective assurance and consulting services designed to add value and enhance the Institute‚Äôs operations. The role supports RHIH in accomplishing its strategic and operational objectives by applying a systematic and disciplined approach to evaluating and improving the effectiveness of risk management, internal controls, and governance processes.

The Internal Auditor will examine financial, operational, and compliance activities across the Institute‚Äôs functional areas‚Äîincluding academic administration, research grants, student services, procurement, IT systems, and healthcare-related operations.

2. Key Responsibilities and Duties

A. Audit Planning and Execution

  • Contribute to the development of a risk-based annual audit plan focused on areas unique to higher education and health institutions (e.g., grant management, student fees, procurement of medical supplies, HR, financial reporting, data privacy).

  • Conduct risk assessments to identify and prioritize high-risk functions.

  • Develop detailed audit programs outlining objectives, scope, and methodologies.

  • Perform audit fieldwork, including staff interviews, process walkthroughs, and transaction testing.

  • Review the accuracy and integrity of financial records, operational data, and compliance with internal policies and applicable laws.

B. Reporting and Follow-Up

  • Document audit work and findings in line with the International Standards for the Professional Practice of Internal Auditing (IIA Standards).

  • Prepare clear and actionable audit reports, outlining issues, their impact, and practical recommendations.

  • Discuss findings with responsible managers to ensure common understanding and agreement on corrective actions.

  • Conduct follow-up audits to confirm implementation and effectiveness of remediation measures.

C. Advisory and Compliance

  • Provide advisory support on designing effective controls for new processes, systems, or major institutional initiatives.

  • Review new and existing institutional policies for completeness, effectiveness, and alignment with risk management best practices.

  • Assess compliance with laws, regulations, accreditation requirements, and sector-specific standards for education and health.

  • Promote ethics and integrity through assessment of code-of-conduct adherence and related controls.

D. Special Investigations and Other Duties

  • Participate in investigations involving suspected fraud, misconduct, or control breakdowns.

  • Coordinate with external auditors to support an efficient and comprehensive audit process.

  • Stay updated on auditing standards, accounting practices, higher education management, and healthcare sector regulations.

E. Performance & Evaluation Assurance (Monitoring & Evaluation Focus)

  • Assess the design and effectiveness of the Institute‚Äôs Monitoring & Evaluation (M&E) frameworks for institutional programs and projects.

  • Verify data integrity for key performance indicators (KPIs) and performance reports.

  • Conduct value-for-money and performance audits to evaluate the efficiency, effectiveness, and impact of academic programs, research projects, and community health initiatives.

  • Review the quality of performance reporting submitted to management, the Governing Body, and external stakeholders.

3. Qualifications and Experience

Education

  • Bachelor‚Äôs degree in Accounting, Finance, or Auditing.

  • Master‚Äôs degree is an added advantage.

Professional Certifications

  • Certified Internal Auditor (CIA) ‚Äì desirable.

  • CPA, ACCA, or an equivalent recognized accounting qualification ‚Äì strongly desirable.

Experience

  • Minimum of 5 years of progressive experience in accounting, financial reporting, internal or external audit, or related fields in large organizations.

  • Experience using QuickBooks accounting software is mandatory.

  • Experience in higher education, healthcare, or non-profit environments is a strong asset.

  • Demonstrated experience conducting risk-based audits and operational reviews.

  • Experience in IT audit and data analytics is desirable.

4. Required Skills and Competencies

Technical Skills

  • Strong knowledge of auditing principles, practices, and IIA Standards.

  • Solid understanding of IFRS/GAAP and institutional financial reporting.

  • Proficiency in data analysis tools (Advanced Excel, ACL, IDEA, Power BI).

  • Knowledge of regulations governing educational institutions and the health sector.

  • Strong working knowledge of accounting software systems.

Soft Skills

  • Excellent analytical and critical-thinking capabilities.

  • Strong written and verbal communication skills.

  • Effective interpersonal skills for interviews and collaboration.

  • High problem-solving aptitude with a proactive approach.

  • Strong integrity, independence, and objectivity.

5. Personal Attributes

Reports to: Program Manager

About Digital Opportunity Trust (DOT)

Digital Opportunity Trust (DOT) is an international non-profit organization headquartered in Ottawa, Canada. For over 23 years, DOT has empowered young women and men across Africa and the Middle East with digital skills, leadership competencies, climate action awareness, and opportunities to participate in an inclusive digital economy.

Since 2010, DOT Rwanda has supported over 120,000 young people through digital literacy programs, 21st-century skills development, and entrepreneurship training. Working closely with government, higher learning institutions, civil society, and private sector partners, DOT strengthens digital capacity and youth leadership across urban and rural communities.

About The RISE Program

The Resilience in Secondary Education (RISE) program is a national initiative targeting 1.1 million out-of-school youth, providing technology-enabled, accredited secondary education. Led by UNICEF, in collaboration with the Ministry of Education and Mastercard Foundation, the RISE consortium includes DOT Rwanda, Carnegie Mellon University (CMU), and partners such as the Imbuto Foundation, CRS, and YWCA.

DOT Rwanda leads the Facilitator Development Pathway, equipping recent graduates with the core digital and facilitation skills to serve as RISE Facilitators. DOT also provides competency frameworks, continuous coaching, and quality assurance to ensure effective guidance of youth through the program.

Position Overview

The M&E Officer is responsible for the data integrity and impact tracking of the RISE Facilitator Development Pathway. This role ensures that data collected from the field‚Äîvia QATs and the LMS‚Äîis accurate, timely, and actionable, supporting adaptive program management and reporting to stakeholders, including UNICEF, the Mastercard Foundation, and the government.

Key Responsibilities

Data Management:

  • Oversee collection and validation of disaggregated participation data (gender, disability, refugee status) to meet equity targets.

System Oversight:

  • Manage district-level analytics dashboards.

  • Monitor facilitator usage of digital curriculum materials.

Reporting:

  • Prepare weekly dashboards, data integrity checks, and comprehensive progress reports.

Field Validation:

  • Conduct audits of data reported by QATs and facilitators.

  • Ensure program fidelity and ‚ÄúRed-Yellow-Green‚Äù performance accuracy.

Learning & Adaptation:

  • Lead internal review meetings.

  • Translate field learnings into systemic improvements.

Required Qualifications

  • Education: Bachelor‚Äôs degree in Statistics, Economics, Data Management, or a related field.

  • Experience: Minimum 3 years in M&E for large-scale development projects; experience with digital data collection tools (ODK, KoboToolbox, etc.) is essential.

  • Analytical Skills: Strong ability to interpret complex datasets and present data clearly to non-technical stakeholders.

  • Attention to Detail: Exceptional commitment to data integrity and risk mitigation.

What DOT Offers

  • Competitive salary within the RISE program budget.

  • Communication and transport allowances for field travel.

  • Opportunity to work within a prestigious multi-partner consortium (UNICEF, REB, NESA, Mastercard Foundation).

  • A dynamic, mission-driven team environment focused on youth empowerment.

How to Apply

Submit your application by clicking on "APPLY BUTTON at the bottom of the page"

Application must include:

  • CV / Resume

  • Higher education certificate (scanned)

  • Copy of Identification Card

DOT Rwanda values diversity and inclusive recruitment. Reasonable accommodations are provided for individuals with disabilities‚Äîplease indicate any needs in your application.

Applications are reviewed on a rolling basis, and the position may be filled before the deadline. Only shortlisted candidates will be contacted.
