title: How to Write a Winning Cover Letter in Rwanda
description:
How to Write a Winning Cover Letter in Rwanda

A cover letter is one of the most important documents when applying for a job in Rwanda. While many job seekers focus heavily on their CV, employers in Rwanda‚Äîespecially NGOs, government institutions, private companies, and international organizations‚Äîoften use the cover letter to assess motivation, communication skills, professionalism, and cultural fit. A well-written cover letter can significantly increase your chances of being shortlisted, even when competition is high.

This guide explains how to write a winning cover letter in Rwanda, taking into account local expectations, professional standards, and practical tips that recruiters value.

1. Understand the Purpose of a Cover Letter

In Rwanda, a cover letter is not just a summary of your CV. It serves several key purposes:

  • To introduce yourself formally to the employer

  • To explain why you are applying for the position

  • To demonstrate how your skills and experience match the job

  • To show your interest in the organization and its mission

  • To reflect your communication skills and professionalism

Recruiters often use the cover letter to decide whether your CV is worth reading. Therefore, it must be clear, relevant, and tailored to the job.

2. Follow the Standard Cover Letter Structure

A winning cover letter in Rwanda should follow a clear and professional structure. Most employers expect a formal letter format.

a) Header and Contact Information

At the top of your letter, include:

  • Your full name

  • Your address (or city and country)

  • Your phone number

  • Your email address

  • Date of application

Below that, include the employer‚Äôs details if available:

  • Name of the organization

  • Department or hiring manager

  • Address or city

This format is especially important for applications to government institutions, NGOs, and international organizations operating in Rwanda.

3. Use a Professional Salutation

Always try to address the letter to a specific person. For example:

  • Dear Hiring Manager,

  • Dear Human Resources Manager,

  • Dear Recruitment Committee,

Avoid informal greetings such as ‚ÄúHello‚Äù or ‚ÄúTo whom it may concern‚Äù unless no other option is available. In Rwanda, respectful and formal language is highly valued in professional communication.

4. Write a Strong Opening Paragraph

The opening paragraph should immediately capture the recruiter‚Äôs attention. Clearly state:

  • The position you are applying for

  • Where you found the job advertisement

  • A brief statement of interest

Example approach:
Mentioning platforms commonly used in Rwanda such as Job in Rwanda, Rwanda Public Service Commission, LinkedIn, NGO websites, or referrals can add credibility.

Avoid generic openings like ‚ÄúI am writing to apply for a job in your organization.‚Äù Instead, be specific and confident.

5. Highlight Relevant Skills and Experience

The body of your cover letter is the most important part. This is where you connect your background to the job requirements.

a) Match the Job Description

Carefully read the job advertisement and identify key skills and qualifications. In Rwanda, employers value:

  • Relevant academic qualifications

  • Practical experience

  • Technical skills

  • Language proficiency (English, French, and/or Kinyarwanda)

  • Ability to work in teams and multicultural environments

Use examples to show how your experience fits the role. For instance:

  • If applying for an NGO role, highlight community engagement, project implementation, monitoring and evaluation, or donor reporting.

  • If applying for a government position, emphasize compliance, policy implementation, accountability, and public service values.

  • If applying for a private company, focus on performance, results, innovation, and efficiency.

b) Be Clear and Honest

Avoid exaggeration. Rwandan employers increasingly verify qualifications and experience. It is better to clearly explain what you have done and what you are capable of learning than to overstate your abilities.

6. Demonstrate Knowledge of the Organization

A winning cover letter in Rwanda shows that you understand the organization and its mission. This is especially important for:

  • NGOs and international organizations

  • Development partners

  • Faith-based institutions

  • Government agencies

Mention:

  • The organization‚Äôs mission or core values

  • Ongoing projects or focus areas

  • How your skills align with their goals

This shows genuine interest and effort, qualities that Rwandan recruiters highly appreciate.

7. Highlight Soft Skills and Values

In Rwanda, employers place strong emphasis on character and work ethic. Soft skills often make the difference between candidates with similar qualifications.

You may highlight:

  • Integrity and accountability

  • Teamwork and collaboration

  • Strong work ethic

  • Adaptability and willingness to learn

  • Respect for diversity and inclusiveness

For roles involving community work or leadership, demonstrating respect for Rwandan culture and values is a major advantage.

8. Write a Convincing Closing Paragraph

The closing paragraph should:

  • Reaffirm your interest in the position

  • Express willingness to attend an interview

  • Mention that your CV is attached

  • Thank the employer for their time

Keep it polite and confident. Avoid sounding desperate or overly aggressive.

End with a professional closing such as:

  • Yours sincerely,

  • Respectfully,

Then sign with your full name.

9. Language and Tone: What Works in Rwanda

  • Use clear and formal English unless the job specifies French or Kinyarwanda.

  • Avoid slang, jokes, or overly casual expressions.

  • Keep sentences concise and well-structured.

  • Check spelling and grammar carefully. Poor language skills often lead to automatic rejection.

If English is not your first language, ask someone to proofread your letter before submission.

10. Length and Formatting

A winning cover letter in Rwanda should:

  • Be one page (3‚Äì5 paragraphs)

  • Use a professional font (Arial, Calibri, or Times New Roman)

  • Font size 11 or 12

  • Proper spacing and margins

Employers appreciate clarity and organization.

11. Customize Every Cover Letter

One of the biggest mistakes job seekers in Rwanda make is sending the same cover letter to multiple employers. Recruiters can easily tell.

Always customize:

  • Job title

  • Organization name

  • Skills and experience highlighted

Customization shows seriousness and professionalism.

Conclusion

Writing a winning cover letter in Rwanda requires more than good writing skills. It requires understanding employer expectations, respecting professional norms, and clearly demonstrating how your skills and values align with the organization‚Äôs needs. By following a clear structure, using formal and respectful language, tailoring your content to each job, and highlighting both technical and soft skills, you significantly improve your chances of success.

A strong cover letter can open doors even in a competitive job market. Take the time to write it well, and it will work in your favor.

title: Officer, Guarantee Monitoring at Development Bank of Rwanda (BRD)
description:
VACANCY ANNOUNCEMENT

The Development Bank of Rwanda (BRD) Plc, the nation‚Äôs sole National Development Bank, plays a critical role in advancing Rwanda‚Äôs Vision 2050. Over the past five years, BRD has achieved substantial growth, contributing meaningfully to socio-economic development, strengthening institutional and human capacity, and promoting best practices in corporate governance and risk management.

BRD is currently rolling out its revised 2024‚Äì2028 strategic plan, which is aligned with Rwanda‚Äôs long-term development priorities. This strategy positions the Bank to generate greater value for its stakeholders by supporting entrepreneurship, addressing market inefficiencies, and driving impactful socio-economic transformation.

The Bank‚Äôs expanded mandate is anchored in four strategic focus areas:

  • Delivering transformational finance

  • Scaling up green financing for a resilient future

  • Driving impact at scale

  • Advancing innovation and technology

To achieve these objectives, BRD continues to strengthen its human capital and institutional capability, reinforcing its status as a center of excellence within the financial sector.

BRD is committed to gender equality and inclusion. Female candidates and persons with disabilities are encouraged to apply.

To support its ambitious vision, BRD seeks qualified professionals to join its team in the following role:

OFFICER, GUARANTEE MONITORING (1 Position)

1. Background Information

Job Title: Officer, Credit Guarantee Monitoring
Department: Credit Guarantee
Reports to: Manager, Credit Guarantee Risk

2. Contract Terms

Fixed-Term Contract: One year, renewable

3. Purpose of the Role

The Credit Guarantee Monitoring Officer is responsible for the daily oversight of guaranteed loan portfolios across Participating Financial Institutions (PFIs). The role ensures the accuracy of PFI reports, adherence to Guarantee Framework Agreements (GFAs), and verification of key performance data‚Äîincluding arrears, claims, and recoveries.

This role requires strong data integrity management, early risk signal identification, validation of claim documentation, tracking recovery progress, and ensuring compliance with guarantee procedures and the operational manual. The Monitoring Officer plays a central role in safeguarding portfolio quality, improving PFI reporting discipline, and supporting effective performance monitoring of the guarantee schemes.

4. Key Responsibilities

  • Review periodic PFI reports on loan performance, arrears, recoveries, and outstanding guarantee exposure.

  • Validate the accuracy, completeness, and compliance of submitted data in line with GFA requirements and guarantee terms.

  • Detect data inconsistencies, reporting gaps, or unusual portfolio trends and follow up with PFIs for clarification or correction.

  • Monitor key portfolio indicators including PAR ratios, concentration levels, and early warning signals.

  • Verify arrears status, repayment patterns, and PFI recovery actions prior to claim submission.

  • Track post-claim recoveries and ensure recoveries are shared according to risk-sharing provisions.

  • Maintain updated recovery tracking sheets and provide regular recovery status updates to the Team Lead.

  • Assess PFI compliance with reporting obligations and escalate recurring non-compliance concerns.

  • Enter and update guarantee portfolio data in the MIS, ensuring accuracy, completeness, and timely reconciliation.

  • Maintain comprehensive monitoring logs, validation trackers, and supporting documentation.

  • Monitor guarantee fee invoices and follow up on overdue or outstanding payments.

  • Collaborate with Operations, Transactions, Risk, Finance, and MIS teams to support coordinated monitoring efforts.

  • Contribute to continuous improvement initiatives by refining monitoring tools, templates, and workflows.

  • Perform any additional tasks assigned by the Team Lead or Management to enhance the monitoring function.

5. Performance Indicators

Performance will be evaluated based on the accuracy, completeness, and timeliness of monitoring activities. Key indicators include:

  • Quality and reliability of validated data and MIS entries

  • Ability to detect early warning risks and ensure strong data integrity

  • Timely validation of claims and effective recovery tracking

  • Engagement and responsiveness of PFIs in addressing reporting or compliance gaps

  • Quality of dashboards, monitoring reports, and contributions to process improvements

  • Effective collaboration and professional communication with stakeholders

7. Qualifications, Skills, and Experience

  • Bachelor‚Äôs degree in finance, economics, business administration, banking, statistics, or a related field.

  • Minimum of three years‚Äô experience in credit monitoring, portfolio analysis, financial reporting, or banking operations‚Äîpreferably within a financial institution or guarantee scheme.

  • Strong understanding of credit risk, arrears analysis, NPL management, and portfolio monitoring indicators.

  • Experience working with large datasets; advanced Excel skills required. Knowledge of MIS or digital reporting tools is an added advantage.

  • Strong analytical and problem-solving abilities with excellent attention to detail.

  • Good communication and report-writing skills, with the ability to engage PFIs and internal teams effectively.

  • Ability to work independently, manage reporting timelines, and follow structured monitoring processes.

  • High levels of integrity, discipline, and commitment to maintaining accurate portfolio records.

Application Guidelines

Interested candidates should apply online via https://www.brd.rw/careers/ and upload a single combined document containing:

  • Curriculum Vitae

  • Copies of academic degrees and professional certificates

  • Motivation letter

  • Names, email addresses, and telephone contacts of three previous supervisors

Only online applications will be considered.

For inquiries (not applications), email: recruitment@brd.rw

Address applications to:
Director, People, Culture and Corporate Services, BRD

Application Deadline: December 19, 2025

BRD offers a competitive and attractive compensation package.
Only candidates who meet the required qualifications and experience will be shortlisted and contacted for interviews.

Issued in Kigali, Monday, December 9, 2025

title: Head of Business and Operations at
description:
VACANCY ANNOUNCEMENT

Background

ACB Plc is a Christian Micro Finance Institution that started its operations in August 2006. It is licensed by the National Bank of Rwanda (BNR). Our vision is to be a leading Christian financial institution that contributes to holistic and sustainable development. Our mission is to bring holistic transformation into the community through quality financial services. Our values are quality service, transparency, integrity and accountability. We are committed to taking financial services closer to the people.

AMASEZERANO Community Banking (ACB) Plc is looking for qualified, competent, committed, proactive and self-motivated individual to occupy the following positions.

HEAD OF BUSINESS AND OPERATIONS

Department: Business & Operations

Reporting to: Managing Director

Number of positions: 1

Job summary

Responsible for driving sustainable business growth and operational excellence performance across the Bank. The role translates strategy into measurable results by overseeing branch and digital operations, revenue growth, cost efficiency, client experience and regulatory compliance, while ensuring responsible finance and strong risk management in line with the institution‚Äôs mission and the National Bank of Rwanda requirements.

Our mission is to provide unsurpassed, safe, and reliable services in air transportation, including strategically linking Rwanda with the outside world while ensuring a fair return on investment. As part of the expansion strategy, we are looking for interested, qualified, and competent candidates to fill the following position:

Job Title:             MCC Engineer

Department:  Technical

Location:             Kigali International Airport

Job Purpose

To improve the overall aircraft performance and continued airworthiness by providing a front line review of fleet operational performance and in depth technical recommendation on current and emergent aircraft/ fleet issue.

To improve aircraft availability by providing continuous monitoring of aircraft status and the identification of fleet production reliability and operational performance issues. To further manage individual AOG events at the request of the Supervisor or Manager MCC.

To ensure that all maintenance including casualties on RwandAir Aircraft is carried out to the highest possible Maintenance Standards and Safety in the most productive and cost effective manner using all available resources at disposal

Ensuring the highest standard of Support, Service and Technical Dispatch Reliability are provided to the RwandAir Operation and RwandAir Customers.

1.      Key Duties and Responsibilities:

a)     Operational

title: Head of Information Technology (Head of IT) at SanlamAllianz General Insurance
description:
SanlamAllianz General Insurance Plc is seeking to recruit a highly skilled, self-driven, and experienced professional to fill the position of Head of Information Technology (Head of IT).

The position reports directly to the Chief Executive Officer. The Head of IT will be responsible for leading the technology strategy, managing infrastructure, and overseeing cybersecurity and digital transformation initiatives within the insurance company. This role ensures that IT systems and processes align with business objectives, regulatory requirements, and industry‚Äôs best practices. The Head of IT will oversee IT operations, manage teams, implement innovative solutions, and ensure the security and reliability of all technology systems.

Key Duties and Responsibilities

IT Strategy & Leadership

  • Develop and execute an IT strategy that aligns with the company‚Äôs business objectives.

  • Lead, mentor, and manage the IT team to ensure high performance and professional growth.

  • Stay updated with emerging technologies and trends in the insurance industry.

  • Collaborate closely with senior leadership and take the lead on driving innovation and transformation using digital tools and technologies.

1. IT Infrastructure & System Management

  • Oversee the implementation, maintenance, and enhancement of IT infrastructure.

  • Ensure the availability, security, and reliability of core insurance applications, including policy administration, claims processing, and underwriting systems.

  • Manage cloud and on-premises IT environments, ensuring scalability and resilience.

  • Ensure efficient IT service management (ITSM) and support employees and business functions.

2. Cybersecurity & Compliance

  • Implement and maintain cybersecurity policies to protect company data and IT assets.

  • Ensure compliance with data protection laws, industry regulations, and IT governance frameworks (e.g., GDPR, ISO 27001).

  • Conduct regular risk assessments and audits to identify and mitigate vulnerabilities.

  • Establish data governance policies to ensure secure and ethical data usage.

3. Digital Transformation & Innovation

  • Lead digital initiatives to enhance operational efficiency and customer experience.

  • Drive the adoption of InsurTech solutions, automation, AI, and data analytics.

  • Oversee the development and optimization of customer-facing digital platforms, such as web portals and mobile applications.

  • Ensure seamless integration of new technologies with existing insurance systems.

3. IT Budgeting & Vendor Management

  • Develop and manage the IT budget, ensuring cost-effective investments.

  • Oversee procurement and vendor relationships for IT software, hardware, and services.

  • Negotiate contracts with technology providers to ensure service quality and compliance.

4. IT Support & Business Continuity.

  • Ensure efficient IT support services for employees and business operations.

  • Develop and maintain disaster recovery and business continuity plans.

  • Implement backup and recovery strategies to safeguard critical business data.

5. Qualifications and Experience

The successful candidate must have:

  • Have a bachelor‚Äôs degree in information technology, computer science, or a related field, with a master‚Äôs degree preferred.

  • At least three years of experience working in managerial position as a senior manager related to Information Technology.

  • Experience in the insurance or financial services industry is highly preferred.

  • Proficient understanding of IT infrastructure and cybersecurity, cloud systems and enterprise level systems.

  • Comfortable with insurance tech platforms like systems for managing policies and claims.

  • Having knowledge of data protection and financial regulation norms is important.

  • Experience managing IT budgets, vendors, and digital transformation projects.

Key Skills and Competencies

  • Strategic Thinking: Ability to align IT strategy with business goals.

  • Leadership & Team Management: Proven ability to lead and mentor IT teams.

  • Cybersecurity & Risk Management: Strong understanding of data security best practices.

  • Project Management: Experience in leading IT projects from planning to execution.

  • Problem-Solving: Analytical mindset to identify and resolve IT challenges.

  • Communication Skills: Ability to communicate complex IT concepts to non-technical stakeholders.

Additional Knowledge & Technical Skills

  • General insurance industry knowledge.

  • Programming skills

  • Proficiency in Oracle and SQL.

  • Report writing expertise

Application Requirements

Interested candidates should submit:

  1. A motivation letter.

  2. An updated CV with three professional references. References must include current or previous direct supervisors, with full names, phone numbers, and email addresses.

  3. Copies of degrees and professional certificates.

  4. Copy of national ID card or passport.

Applications should be submitted no later than December 11th, 2025. Please click on the ‚ÄúApply‚Äù button to complete your application.

Only applicants who fully meet the above requirements will be contacted.

N.B: Women are highly encouraged to apply to this position.

Pharo Foundation is a mission-driven, impact-oriented organization focused on economic development in Africa. It operates through:

  1. Pharo Development: Non-profit initiatives in Education, Water, and Economic Productivity.

  2. Pharo Ventures: For-profit investments to support critical value chains.

The Foundation is active in Rwanda, running Pharo School Kigali and teacher capacity-building programs. It has 700+ employees across Ethiopia, Kenya, Rwanda, and Somaliland, with headquarters in Nairobi and a liaison office in London.

Role Overview

The IT Officer manages and maintains all technology systems for the Foundation Office, Venture Office, and Pharo School Kigali. The role ensures uninterrupted IT functionality, supports staff and students, oversees school digital platforms, and ensures cybersecurity and data compliance. The IT Officer works closely with the Global IT Director.

Key Responsibilities

1. IT Infrastructure & System Management

  • Install, configure, and maintain computers, printers, networks, and other IT equipment.

  • Ensure uninterrupted internet, Wi-Fi, and LAN connectivity.

  • Maintain servers, cloud services, user accounts, backups, and shared drives.

2. Technical Support for Staff and Students

  • Provide support for teachers, administrative staff, and Foundation team members.

  • Install and update operating systems, productivity tools, and educational software.

  • Manage email systems (Microsoft 365 / Google Workspace) and licenses.

5. Cybersecurity & Data Protection

  • Maintain antivirus systems, firewalls, and access controls.

  • Conduct backups and ensure safe handling of student and organizational data.

  • Support compliance with IT and data protection policies.

6. IT Asset Management

  • Maintain inventory of IT equipment for offices and school.

  • Coordinate procurement, repair, replacement, and disposal of IT assets.

  • Prepare reports on IT usage, system health, and resource needs.

7. Training & Capacity Building

  • Train staff and teachers on IT tools, data management, and digital safety.

  • Support digital literacy initiatives for students.

  • Develop user guides and maintain system documentation.

8. Collaboration & Reporting

  • Work with Foundation leadership, school management, and vendors.

  • Provide updates on IT performance, incidents, and project progress.

Qualifications & Experience

  • Technical Skills:

    • Windows/MacOS/Linux operating systems

    • Networking (TCP/IP, DHCP, DNS, Wi-Fi troubleshooting)

King Faisal Hospital Rwanda (KFH-R)

King Faisal Hospital Rwanda is undergoing an exciting phase of growth as it embraces a new strategic direction. The hospital continues to build on its strong reputation for compassionate, patient-centered care and highly skilled medical professionals, particularly in specialized medical and surgical services.

King Faisal Hospital Kigali invites qualified and motivated candidates to apply for the position below:

POSITION: Infection Prevention and Control (IPC) Officer

EDUCATION AND EXPERIENCE

title: Internal Audit Manager
description:
VACANCY ANNOUNCEMENT

Background

ACB Plc is a Christian Micro Finance Institution that started its operations in August 2006. It is licensed by the National Bank of Rwanda (BNR). Our vision is to be a leading Christian financial institution that contributes to holistic and sustainable development. Our mission is to bring holistic transformation into the community through quality financial services. Our values are quality service, transparency, integrity and accountability. We are committed to taking financial services closer to the people.

AMASEZERANO Community Banking (ACB) Plc is looking for qualified, competent, committed, proactiveand self-motivated individual to occupy the following positions.

INTERNAL AUDIT MANAGER

Department: Internal Control

Reporting to: Board of Directors

Number of positions: 1

Job summary:

Responsible for planning, executing and overseeing audit activities (financial, operational, compliance, IT) within the Bank. The role ensures that the institution has effective internal controls, risk management, governance, and compliance with applicable laws, regulations, industry best practices, and internal policies. The incumbent will lead the audit team, liaise with senior management and the audit committee, and contribute to enhancing the control environment and operational efficiency.

I. KEY ROLES AND RESPONSIBILITIES 

  • Develop and implement an annual risk-based audit plan covering branches, departments, support functions, IT systems, and high-risk areas;

  • Lead audit engagements from planning to reporting: define audit scope, objectives, methodology; supervise audit fieldwork, review audit work-papers; compile and present audit reports with findings, recommendations and management responses;

  • Evaluate the adequacy and effectiveness of internal controls, governance and risk management processes; identify control weaknesses, inefficiencies, non-compliance and areas for cost/operational improvement;

  • Monitor implementation of audit recommendations and perform follow-up reviews to ensure agreed actions are taken;

  • Manage and coach the audit team, assign engagements, monitor progress, review work, develop capacity, and ensure quality of work;

  • Liaise with senior management, business unit heads, external auditors and regulators; present findings and advice, support the audit committee or equivalent oversight body; 

  • Ensure audit activities are aligned with regulatory requirements (e.g., central bank/financial sector regulation in Rwanda), industry standards (e.g., International Standards on Auditing (ISA) where applicable), and internal policies/procedures;

  • Promote continuous improvement of audit methods and techniques (including use of data analytics, IT audit tools), update audit manuals and templates accordingly;

  • Prepare periodic management reports on audit results, key audit issues, trends, emerging risks, and status of corrective actions; 

  • Contribute to the strategic direction of the internal audit function and ensure alignment with the institution‚Äôs objectives, culture and risk appetite;

  • Perform any other task assigned by the supervisor; 

II. REQUIRED SKILLS AND EXPERIENCE 

  • Holder of a bachelor‚Äôs/master‚Äôs degree in Accounting or Finance. 

  • Professional certification such as Certified Public Accountant (CPA) is a must.

  • Minimum of 4 years of significant audit experience in either external audit firm and/or internal audit function, preferably in a financial institution

  • Prior experience in a supervisory or managerial role leading audit engagements or managing a team;

  • Understanding of financial services (micro-finance/ banking/financial institutions) operations, risks, and regulatory environment is highly desirable;

  • Familiarity with relevant accounting standards such as IFRS, Internal auditing standards (ISA), risk and internal control frameworks; 

  • Proficiency in audit software, data analytics tools, Microsoft Office (Excel, Word, PowerPoint). 

  • Working knowledge of Finance and Accounting Policies and Procedures preferred with the ability to quickly assimilate specific finance policy knowledge

  • Strong analytical skills include the ability to spot, assess and address risk, materiality and interdependencies and translate it into impact analysis for the financial reporting and recommendations for improvement

  • Strong communication skills presenting internal control and risk matters in an understandable way across various forums and levels of the organization with the right level of detail. 

  • Knowledge of sound internal control principles and demonstrated ability to provide solutions to control issues

  • Strong oral and written communication skills, including sound presentational skills

  • Strong presentation skills with the ability to present and interact with various levels of management

  • Adaptable to working in a fast paced, ever-changing environment 

  • Striving for continuous improvement and optimization 

  • Ability to work both individually, and within a team environment, build strong relationships and maintain rapport with cross-functional business units, Internal Control teams and with external consultants

  • Ability to manage projects, with attention to detail on multiple concurrent tasks, while meeting various deadlines

  • Fluency in English and Kinyarwanda 

How to apply

The vacancies are open from 4th to 19th December 2025. The interested candidates should submit their application documents (Application letter, updated CV, Academic certificates, ID copy, current criminal record certificate and original church recommendation letter signed by your church Pastor) to the ACB Plc via company email amasezerano@acb.rw, not later than 19th December 2025 (05:00 pm).

Note:Only shortlisted candidates will be contacted for the written and oral tests. If you do not hear from us 2 weeks from the closing date, consider your application unsuccessful.

Eraste NSENGIYUMVA 

Managing Director

title: TECHNICAL ADVISOR ‚Äì AI ENGINEER  at Clinton Health Access Initiative (CHAI) ‚Äì Rwanda
description:
JOB VACANCY: TECHNICAL ADVISOR ‚Äì AI ENGINEER (2 POSITIONS)

Organization: Clinton Health Access Initiative (CHAI) ‚Äì Rwanda

Program: Digital Health
Duty Station: Kigali, Rwanda
Employment Type: Full-Time (Paid)
Start Date: Immediate

About CHAI

The Clinton Health Access Initiative, Inc. (CHAI) is a global health organization dedicated to saving lives and reducing the burden of disease in low- and middle-income countries. CHAI works closely with governments to strengthen health systems, improve access to essential medicines, and support sustainable healthcare delivery.

In Rwanda, CHAI partners with the Ministry of Health (MoH) and the Rwanda Social Security Board (RSSB) to advance Universal Health Coverage (UHC) through health system strengthening, primary health care reforms, workforce development, financing, and digital health innovation.

Position Overview

CHAI Rwanda is seeking two (2) highly skilled AI Engineers to support the Ministry of Health‚Äôs National Health Intelligence Center (NHIC) in the design, development, and deployment of artificial intelligence (AI) solutions that strengthen Rwanda‚Äôs health system.

The AI Engineers will contribute to the development of scalable, secure, and interoperable AI systems that transform health data into actionable insights for decision-making, service delivery, and public health planning. The role focuses on production-grade AI system development, MLOps, integration with national digital health platforms, and clinical validation.

The successful candidates will be seconded to NHIC and report to the NHIC/Health AI Lead and the CHAI Digital Health Program Manager, working closely with data scientists and digital health teams.

Key Responsibilities

1. AI Model Development & Optimization

  • Design, develop, train, and optimize machine learning and deep learning models.

  • Perform data preprocessing, feature engineering, model validation, tuning, and optimization.

  • Develop explainable AI pipelines to support clinical trust and regulatory transparency.

  • Apply best practices in version control, experiment tracking, and reproducible ML workflows.

2. Deployment, MLOps & Monitoring

  • Deploy AI models into secure and scalable production environments.

  • Establish monitoring systems for model performance, data drift, and concept drift.

  • Implement automated retraining, rollback mechanisms, and release management.

  • Optimize inference performance, reliability, and cost efficiency.

3. System Integration & Interoperability

  • Integrate AI solutions with national digital health platforms (EMRs, HMIS, LMIS).

  • Implement interoperability standards using APIs, HL7/FHIR, and MoH-recommended architectures.

  • Develop secure real-time and batch data pipelines for AI inference.

4. Data Management, Quality & Security

  • Collaborate with NHIC data teams to manage structured and unstructured datasets.

  • Ensure data quality, bias detection, and representativeness checks.

  • Implement secure data handling, encryption, access controls, and audit logging.

  • Maintain dataset documentation and data lineage.

5. Model Evaluation, Clinical Validation & Regulatory Support

  • Conduct rigorous model testing for accuracy, fairness, and clinical relevance.

  • Support clinical pilots and facility-level validation.

  • Prepare technical documentation for ethics, regulatory, and audit reviews.

  • Perform error analysis and continuous model improvement.

6. Documentation & Knowledge Sharing

  • Produce comprehensive technical documentation for AI systems and workflows.

  • Contribute to reports, concept notes, donor updates, and system design briefs.

  • Support development of user guides, SOPs, and training materials.

7. Collaboration & Technical Advisory

  • Collaborate with health sector stakeholders and digital health teams.

  • Participate in AI technical working groups and review sessions.

  • Provide AI engineering input for grants, research initiatives, and partnerships.

8. Continuous Learning & Innovation

  • Stay updated on emerging AI technologies and tools.

  • Propose innovative, high-impact AI use cases for the health sector.

  • Support continuous improvement of national AI infrastructure.

Required Qualifications

Education

  • Master‚Äôs degree or higher in Artificial Intelligence, Computer Engineering, Data Science, Biomedical Engineering, Health Informatics, or a closely related field.

Experience

  • 4‚Äì5 years of experience in applied machine learning and production-grade AI systems.

  • Proven experience deploying and maintaining AI or healthcare IT systems in real-world environments.

Technical Skills

  • Strong experience with APIs, data pipelines, ML frameworks, and system integration.

  • Hands-on experience across the full Large Language Model (LLM) lifecycle.

  • Advanced knowledge of reinforcement learning techniques.

  • Experience designing scalable model evaluation frameworks.

  • Strong engineering skills for deployment, monitoring, and maintenance of AI systems.

How to Apply

Interested candidates should by Clicking to APPLY BUTTON

title: Program Manager at Digital Opportunity Trust (DOT) Rwanda
description:
Call for Applications: Program Manager ‚Äì RISE Facilitator Development Pathway

Location: Kigali, Rwanda
Application Deadline: Sunday, 11th January 2026, 05:00 PM GMT+2

Position: Program Manager
Reports to: DOT Rwanda Leadership
Type: Full-time, Term Contract
Salary: Competitive, based on experience
Start Date: Immediate / January 2026

About Digital Opportunity Trust (DOT)

Digital Opportunity Trust (DOT) is an international non-profit organization headquartered in Ottawa, Canada. For over 23 years, DOT has empowered young women and men across Africa and the Middle East with digital skills, leadership competencies, climate action awareness, and opportunities to participate in an inclusive digital economy.

Since 2010, DOT Rwanda has supported over 120,000 young people through digital literacy programs, 21st-century skills development, and entrepreneurship training. DOT works closely with government, higher learning institutions, civil society, and private sector partners to strengthen digital capacity and youth leadership across urban and rural communities.

About The RISE Program

The Resilience in Secondary Education (RISE) program targets 1.1 million out-of-school youth, providing technology-enabled, accredited secondary education. Led by UNICEF, in collaboration with the Ministry of Education and Mastercard Foundation, the RISE consortium includes DOT Rwanda, Carnegie Mellon University (CMU), and implementing partners such as the Imbuto Foundation, CRS, and YWCA.

DOT Rwanda leads the Facilitator Development Pathway, equipping recent graduates with the digital and facilitation skills required to serve as RISE Facilitators. DOT is responsible for designing the competency framework, providing continuous coaching, and ensuring quality delivery across the program.

Position Overview

The Program Manager (PM) is the strategic lead for the Facilitator Development Pathway, responsible for connecting university graduates to out-of-school youth nationwide. The PM provides operational oversight for a three-tiered support system (Facilitators, Quality Assurance Technicians, Program Officers) while ensuring high-quality delivery in a high-speed rollout environment.

Key Responsibilities

Strategic Partnership & Alignment

  • Serve as the DOT Rwanda focal point for the REB-led RISE Facilitator Training and Development Task Force.

  • Ensure facilitator development aligns with the REB Teacher Professional Development Framework.

  • Coordinate with UNICEF, CMU, Imbuto Foundation, CRS, and YWCA to harmonize curriculum, recruitment, and site readiness.

  • Represent DOT Rwanda in high-level technical working groups.

Operational Management & Training Delivery

  • Oversee the 4-phase blended training model: onboarding, self-paced online learning, virtual sessions, and Practical Demo Days.

  • Manage program budget, ensuring cost-efficiency, transparency, and compliance with UNICEF and Mastercard Foundation requirements.

  • Lead recruitment, onboarding, and performance management of central support staff.

Quality Assurance & Mentorship

  • Provide strategic oversight of Quality Assurance Technicians (QATs) to ensure all facilitators receive monthly coaching visits.

  • Monitor the QA framework and prioritize support for underperforming learning sites.

  • Lead monthly and end-of-semester review meetings to translate field data into adaptive program improvements.

  • Institutionalize inclusive pedagogy and gender-responsive facilitation within the education ecosystem.

Required Qualifications & Experience

  • 3‚Äì5 years managing large-scale education or youth development programs in Rwanda.

  • Strong knowledge of Competence-Based Curriculum (CBC), digital pedagogy, and inclusive facilitation for marginalized groups.

  • Proven ability to manage multi-million dollar budgets.

  • Experience collaborating with government agencies (MINEDUC, REB, NESA) and international NGOs.

  • Proficiency with Learning Management Systems (LMS) and data-driven decision-making.

Core Competencies:

  • Ability to manage a fast-paced rollout and meet tight delivery timelines.

What DOT Offers

  • Competitive salary within the RISE program budget.

Solid‚ÄôAfrica delivers a comprehensive nutrition access program that includes the Gemura Feeding Program, which supplies nutritious meals to hospital patients and school children; the Sustainable Agriculture Program, which supports local farmers and strengthens the food supply chain; and the Nutrition Education Program, which promotes healthy dietary choices through education and awareness. 

Through its Community Benefit Company (CBC), Solid‚ÄôAfrica also generates income to subsidize its non-profit initiatives, ensuring financial sustainability. Additionally, Solid‚ÄôAfrica‚Äôs Institute of Culinary Arts and Nutrition (ICAN) provides specialized training that blends nutrition science and culinary arts to empower hospitality professionals. Position

Number of Staff

Responsibilities

Requirements 

Storekeeper

1

title: Monitoring and Evaluation Officer at SOS Children's Villages Rwanda
description:
VACANCY ANNOUNCEMENT

Position: Monitoring and Evaluation Officer

Number of Positions: One (1)
Contract Type: Fixed-Term
Duty Station: Byumba Program Location
Reports To: Head of Location
Application Deadline: 19 December 2025 (5:00 PM)

About SOS Children‚Äôs Villages Rwanda

Founded in 1949, SOS Children‚Äôs Villages is an international social development organization dedicated to protecting the rights and improving the lives of vulnerable children worldwide. Operating in over 130 countries, the organization provides family-based care for orphaned, abandoned, and at-risk children while supporting young people to become self-reliant and contributing members of society.

In Rwanda, SOS Children‚Äôs Villages Rwanda functions as an affiliate of SOS Children‚Äôs Villages International. Through family strengthening, alternative care, youth empowerment, and community development initiatives, the organization contributes to sustainable child, youth, and family wellbeing. To strengthen programme quality at the Byumba Program Location, SOS Children‚Äôs Villages Rwanda is seeking a qualified Monitoring and Evaluation Officer.

Mission of the Position

Job Purpose

The Monitoring and Evaluation (M&E) Officer plays a key leadership role in the design, coordination, and implementation of a comprehensive Monitoring and Evaluation system at the program location. The role ensures that programmes and projects are effectively planned, monitored, evaluated, and documented in line with organizational standards and result-based management (RBM) principles.

Working closely with programme teams, the M&E Officer supports proposal development, concept note preparation, staff capacity building, data quality management, and evidence-based decision-making. The position also supports the Head of Location in preparing quarterly, biannual, and annual reports while maintaining high data quality standards within the programme database (PDB2).

Key Duties and Responsibilities

  • Ensure strict adherence to SOS Children‚Äôs Villages‚Äô M&E guidelines, tools, and templates across the program location.

  • Lead and actively participate in planning, monitoring, evaluation, reporting, and research activities, ensuring compliance with ethical standards.

  • Coordinate results-based management (RBM) planning and reporting processes.

  • Promote impact reporting through high-quality documentation of stories of change, best practices, and lessons learned.

  • Provide direct technical support to programme staff in developing project M&E plans.

  • Offer technical guidance for programme baseline studies and evaluations.

  • Support the development of strategic and annual plans, including target setting, indicator development, and alignment with national strategies.

  • Lead the development and improvement of data collection and monitoring tools for child, youth, family, and community development.

  • Maintain and regularly update the programme location database (PDB2).

  • Strengthen monitoring and evaluation procedures and impact indicators to ensure project success.

  • Monitor and analyze programme performance with a focus on quality, sustainability, and results.

  • Advise programme teams on strategies to improve effectiveness and efficiency.

  • In collaboration with the National M&E Manager and Head of Location, identify capacity gaps and build staff capacity in programme quality and RBM.

  • Ensure cross-cutting themes such as child safeguarding, advocacy, gender equality, and disability inclusion are integrated into all programmes.

Required Qualifications

  • Bachelor‚Äôs degree in Project Management, Business Administration, Management, Economics, Development Studies, or a related field.

  • Minimum of three (3) years of relevant professional experience in Monitoring and Evaluation.

  • Proven experience and documented track record in programme planning, monitoring, and evaluation.

Required Competencies and Skills

  • Strong commitment to SOS Children‚Äôs Villages‚Äô vision, mission, and strategic objectives.

  • Cultural sensitivity, gender awareness, and adaptability.

  • Ability to manage multiple tasks, prioritize effectively, and meet deadlines in a multi-reporting environment.

  • Strong relationship-building skills to support learning, collaboration, and programme improvement.

  • In-depth knowledge of planning, monitoring, information systems, and organizational development.

  • Proven ability to identify capacity-building needs and deliver effective trainings.

  • Strong analytical, problem-solving, and critical-thinking skills.

  • Demonstrated experience in proposal development and results documentation.

  • Ability to generate learning evidence for programme quality improvement and decision-making.

  • Advanced computer skills, including Excel, Word, database management systems, Power BI, or other statistical software.

  • Ability to work independently with minimal supervision.

  • Excellent teamwork and interpersonal skills.

  • Experience working with an international NGO is an added advantage.

  • Fluency in English and Kinyarwanda; working knowledge of French is an asset.

  • Excellent written and verbal communication skills in English are mandatory.

How to Apply

Qualified candidates are invited to submit their applications no later than 19 December 2025 at 5:00 PM.

Applications should include:

  • Application letter

  • Curriculum Vitae (CV) with three traceable referees

  • Copy of National Identity Card

title: Training and Logistics Coordinator at Signalytic
description:
Job Title: Training and Logistics Coordinator

Reports To: Country Director

Location: Kigali, Rwanda (with frequent travel to installation and support sites)

Job Type: Full-time

Why Join Signalytic?

At Signalytic, you will join a committed, forward-thinking team positioned at the intersection of technology and global health impact. We offer a highly collaborative environment where your contributions are valued, and professional growth opportunities are abundant. We seek a dedicated individual prepared to step into a critical support role within our expanding operations.

Organizational Profile

Signalytic provides essential digital health infrastructure for remote healthcare facilities across Rwanda. The company‚Äôs S+ Platform is a robust, solar-powered system specifically engineered to operate in areas challenged by unreliable internet and power. The system integrates a mini-server, a tablet, a solar panel, and a Wi-Fi router to establish a local network and host applications. Through this technology, Signalytic is digitizing health information, enabling real-time data sharing, and strengthening supply chain management to prevent medicine stockouts at the last mile.

Role Summary

The Training and Logistics Coordinator is a pivotal project manager responsible for the successful execution of two critical, interconnected functions: managing a large-scale technical training program and overseeing all end-to-end logistics for project materials under the GAVI Project. This dual mandate requires a candidate who can collaborate with technical teams to develop a rigorous, high-quality certification curriculum, while simultaneously orchestrating the complex operational and material supply chain. 

Key Responsibilities

1. Operational Coordination

Manage all non-technical, administrative, and logistical components necessary for successful training delivery and project material flow.

  • Program Scheduling: Develop and maintain the comprehensive training calendar, strategically staggering cohorts to align with supervisor availability, equipment shipment arrivals, and overall go-live targets.

  • Training Operations: Secure appropriate training venues, power access, workspace, and secure storage. Organize all necessary support services, including catering, transport, and accommodation for trainers and trainees.

  • Material Supply Chain Management:

    • Manage the secure warehousing and distribution of all project materials to technical teams and service providers.

    • Conduct customs clearance procedures for all GAVI project shipments.

    • Coordinate with procurement and technical teams to source and purchase required materials from the local market.

  • Transportation and Safety:

    • Coordinate the safe transportation and security of all goods.

    • Arrange safe transport and manage all on-site safety for trainees, field technicians, and training materials.

  • Procurement Support: Collaborate with the procurement team to manage the in-country procurement of training consumables, tools, Personal Protective Equipment (PPE), SIM cards, and the assembly of training mockups and live/demo PowerMax units.

  • Ad-hoc Support: Execute all other essential logistical work not explicitly defined.

2. Monitoring, Reporting, and Risk Management

Ensure the project remains on track by providing clear, data-driven updates and proactively mitigating risks.

  • Risk Mitigation: Proactively identify, track, and manage operational risks related to material changes, venue availability, scheduling conflicts, and shipment delays.

  • Stakeholder Communication: Prepare documentation and contribute training outcomes for formal communications, including client and government reporting.

Candidate Profile

Required Qualifications

  • Education: A diploma or bachelor's degree in Project Management, Business Administration, Logistics, or a related technical discipline.

  • Experience: A minimum of 2 years of proven, demonstrated experience in project coordination, logistics management, or organizing technical training programs within a professional environment, particularly with field teams.

  • Core Skills: Exceptional organizational and multitasking abilities with a proven aptitude for prioritizing complex, competing demands. Demonstrated ability to coordinate with technical subject matter experts effectively.

  • Technical Proficiency: Competence in using the Microsoft Office Suite (Word, Excel) and project management tools (e.g., Google Sheets, calendars).

  • Language: Excellent written and verbal communication skills in both English and Kinyarwanda.

Preferred Qualifications

  • Local Knowledge: Established familiarity with Rwanda's local vendors, transport, and logistics networks.

  • Industry Experience: Direct experience coordinating training for technical, solar, or health sector projects.

  • Interpersonal Skills: A strong collaborator with a track record of building and maintaining effective relationships with trainers, technical leads, and external logistics partners.

How to Apply

  • If this opportunity speaks to you, please fill out this form

  • Applications will be reviewed on a rolling basis. The final submission deadline is 5 PM CAT on December 15, 2025.

  • Please note: Only candidates with the qualifications and experience directly relevant to the role will be shortlisted and contacted.

description:
RwandAir Ltd is the flag carrier airline of Rwanda. It operates domestic and international services to East Africa, Central Africa, West Africa, Southern Africa, Europe and the Middle East from its main base at Kigali International Airport. Our mission is to provide unsurpassed, safe, and reliable services in air transportation, including strategically linking Rwanda with the outside world while ensuring a fair return on investment. As part of the expansion strategy, we are looking for interested, qualified, and competent candidates to fill the following position:

Job Title:             Compliance Specialist

Reports to:         Manager Enterprise, Risk and Compliance

Department:            Compliance and Risk

Location:             Kigali International Airport (KIA)

 

Job Purpose

The Compliance Specialist is responsible for supporting the organization‚Äôs compliance framework by monitoring business activities, conducting audits, and maintaining adherence to applicable laws, regulations, and internal policies. The role ensures that compliance risks are identified, addressed, and reported, while promoting ethical practices and safeguarding the organization‚Äôs integrity and reputation.

 

1.      Key Duties and Responsibilities:

¬∑        Monitor business operations and activities to ensure compliance with laws, regulations, and internal policies.

¬∑        Conduct compliance audits, inspections, and investigations, documenting findings and recommending corrective actions.

¬∑        Assist in the development, implementation, and updating of compliance policies, procedures, and training programs.

¬∑        Maintain compliance records, registers, and databases in alignment with organizational standards.

¬∑        Stay current with changes in the regulatory environment and advise on their impact to the organization.

¬∑        Support regulatory filings, submissions, and responses to external audits or inquiries.

¬∑        Collaborate with departments such as Legal, HR, IT, Finance, and Operations to address compliance issues.

¬∑        Clearly communicate compliance requirements to both technical and non-technical stakeholders.

¬∑        Prepare and present compliance reports for management review.

¬∑        Support the confidential reporting process and assist in investigations of compliance concerns.

¬∑        Contribute to embedding compliance within daily business practices across all departments.

¬∑        Provide insights to the Manager Risk, Compliance and Documentation on emerging compliance issues and potential risks.

¬∑        Support organizational readiness for audits.

¬∑        Help promote an enterprise-wide culture of ethics, integrity, and accountability.

 

2.      About You ‚Äì Minimum Standard Qualifications; Essential

¬∑        Bachelor‚Äôs degree in Business, Law, Finance, or related field (mandatory).

¬∑      ProfessionalcertificationsuchasCertifiedCompliance&EthicsProfessional(CCEP),Certified Regulatory Compliance Manager (CRCM), or equivalent is an advantage.

 

3.      About You ‚Äì Other Desired Competencies & Skills; Previous Experience:

Essential

¬∑        Minimum of 3 years‚Äô experience in compliance, legal, audit, or regulatory roles.

¬∑        Understanding of compliance frameworks and standards relevant to the aviation industry (e.g., ISO 37301, ISO 9001, IOSA/ISAGO, RCAA/ICAO requirements).

¬∑        Strong organizational and documentation management skills.

¬∑        Excellent written and verbal communication abilities.

¬∑        High ethical standards, integrity, and attention to detail.

¬∑        Ability to review complex documentation, identify discrepancies, and recommend preventive measures.

¬∑        Experience in managing compliance initiatives, audits, or remediation plans within deadlines.

 

4.      How to Apply:

¬∑        An application letter addressed to the Chief HR & Administration Officer;

¬∑        Recent Curriculum Vitae;

¬∑        Copies of Notarized Degree/Diploma certificates

¬∑        Relevant certificates;

¬∑        Copies of academic papers;

¬∑        A photocopy of the Passport/National ID;

¬∑        Three referees

 

The deadline for submitting application documents (Only PDF Format) is December 16, 2025. Please apply via the link: https://erecruitment.rwandair.com/.

title: HR & Admin Executive at ENVIROSERVE RWANDA GREEN PARK Ltd
description:
POSITION SUMMARY

The HR &Admin Manager is responsible for managing the complete employee lifecycle from onboarding to offboarding, with primary accountability for HR operations and HR documentation management. This role will ensure full compliance with Rwanda labour laws while maintaining operational efficiency and positive employee experience throughout their employment journey.

KEY ACCOUNTABILITIES

1. HR OPERATIONS & SYSTEMS

  • Manage day-to-day HR operations and employee lifecycle processes

  • Lead and manage HR system and automation of HR processes

  • Maintain employee records in physical and digital formats

  • Process monthly attendance and leave management through automated systems

  • Handle employment contracts, renewals, and documentation

  • Support payroll processing in coordination with Finance team

  • Prepare monthly HR reports and analytics for management and HO

  • Develop operational SOPs and process documentation

  • Monitor the implementation of the performance appraisal and ensuring that mid- term and annual appraisals are carried out in a timely manner and followed up.

2. COMPLIANCE & POLICY DEVELOPMENT 

  • Ensure full compliance with Rwanda labour laws and regulations

  • Develop and localize HR policies in coordination with UAE HO

  • Maintain statutory records and documentation

  • Manage RSSB, PAYE, and other statutory requirements

  • Lead HR audits and compliance checks

  • Handle employee queries and grievances through formal channels

3. RECRUITMENT & TRAINING 

  • Coordinate recruitment activities for all positions supporting growth plans

  • Enhance ES Training Program for fresh graduates

  • Develop structured onboarding program

  • Liaise with plant supervisors for training coordination

  • Maintain comprehensive training records

  • Track and report training ROI and effectiveness metrics

  • Build talent pipeline for expansion needs

4. EMPLOYEE RELATIONS & ENGAGEMENT (10%)

  • Design and execute employee engagement calendar

  • Support performance management cycle Maintain positive work environment (protecting zero-attrition record)

  • Coordinate staff events (Labor Day, annual townhall, engagement activities)

  • Implement employee feedback mechanisms

  • Conduct stay interviews and engagement surveys

5. STAKEHOLDER MANAGEMENT (10%)

  • Maintain professional and diplomatic communication with government authorities

  • Coordinate effectively with Finance, IT, Admin, and Operations teams

  • Escalate critical issues, delays, or risks to MD & Head of HR with recommended solutions

  • Build and maintain positive relationships with internal and external stakeholders

  • Represent HR department professionally in all interactions

  • Support HR projects and strategic initiatives as assigned

  • HR reporting monthly, quarterly and annual as required to HR HO

6. GENERAL ADMINISTRATIVE DUTIES

¬∑ Responsible for all administrative related matters

  • Manage day-to-day office operations; oversee and coordinate overall office activities 

  • Oversee and ensure the effective use of office space and assist with managing facilities and ensure optimal use and determining future needs

  • Provide comprehensive administrative support to the MD, coordinate and maintain the MD‚Äôs calendar,
    scheduling appointments, meetings, and events.

QUALIFICATIONS & REQUIREMENTS

Education & Experience

  • Bachelor‚Äôs degree in human resources, business administration, or related field

  • 3-5 years of experience in HR and administration operations

  • Experience in manufacturing or industrial sector preferred

  • HRIS experience highly desirable

Technical Skills

  • Advanced proficiency in MS Office Suite (Excel, Word, PowerPoint, Outlook)

  • Strong database management and reporting capabilities

  • Basic understanding of payroll and statutory compliance

  • Knowledge of Rwanda labour laws (preferred)

Core Competencies

  • Strong organizational and administrative skills

  • Attention to detail with zero tolerance for errors

  • Professional business communication skills in English (written and verbal)

  • Strong sense of accountability and ownership

  • Ability to maintain strict confidentiality

  • Customer service mindset with focus on employee experience

  • Collaborative team player with ability to work independently

  • Cultural sensitivity and adaptability

Personal Attributes

  • Uncompromising integrity and professional ethics

  • Calm and composed under pressure with ability to handle urgent situations

  • Diplomatic and tactful in dealings with government authorities

  • Adaptable to changing regulations, business needs, and priorities

  • Self-motivated with continuous learning mindset

  • Professional demeanour and appearance

WORKING CONDITIONS

  • Office-based role with regular visits to Bugesera facility

  • Standard business hours with flexibility required for urgent/ad-hoc requirements

  • Handling of confidential and sensitive employee information requiring discretion

Applicants are required to submit the following documents:

  1. Updated Curriculum Vitae (CV):
    Clearly indicating academic background, professional experience, key competencies, and at least three professional referees.

  2. Cover Letter:

  3. Copy of Academic Certificates:
    Including degree certificates, diplomas, and any other relevant professional training or HR-related certifications.

  4. Recommendation or Reference Letters:
    At least one recent reference letter from a previous employer or supervisor 

  5. Professional Certifications (if available):
    Such as CIPD, SHRM, CHRP, or any other HR-related certification.

  6. Additional Supporting Documents:

Note: 

All applications, accompanied by the required supporting documents, should be submitted
to Via Apply button not later than 22 December 2025.

title: Project Coordinator Project at RATA//Project: Inclusion of Students with Disabilities in TVET Schools through Assistive Technology.
description:
Job Title: Project Coordinator

Project: Inclusion of Students with Disabilities in TVET Schools through Assistive Technology
Organization: Rwanda Assistive Technology Access (RATA)
Donor: Swiss Agency for Development and Cooperation (SDC)
Location: Kigali, Rwanda (with nationwide travel)
Contract Duration: January 2026 ‚Äì December 2026
Start Date: As soon as possible
Application Deadline: 5 January 2026

About RATA

Rwanda Assistive Technology Access (RATA) is an NGO established in 2018, dedicated to ensuring accessible Assistive Technology (AT) for persons with disabilities. Its vision is to foster a community where students and individuals with disabilities can learn and live independently through AT.

In collaboration with the Rwanda TVET Board (RTB) and supported by SDC, RATA is implementing a one-year project to improve access to quality Technical and Vocational Education and Training (TVET) for students with disabilities through Assistive Technology integration in 100 TVET schools nationwide.

Purpose of the Position

The Project Coordinator will manage, coordinate, and oversee the project, ensuring timely delivery of activities, adherence to scope and budget, and compliance with donor, RATA, and RTB requirements.

Key Responsibilities

Project Planning and Coordination

  • Lead planning, coordination, and day-to-day management of project activities.

  • Develop and update work plans, schedules, and coordination matrices.

  • Coordinate with RTB, TVET schools, trainers, consultants, and other stakeholders.

  • Ensure smooth implementation of project phases, including ToTs, teacher training, awareness campaigns, AT distribution, and resource center establishment.

Stakeholder Engagement and Partnerships

  • Serve as primary liaison between RATA and RTB.

  • Coordinate with TVET schools, district authorities, MINEDUC structures, OPDs, and community actors.

  • Support advocacy and awareness campaigns for inclusive TVET enrollment.

  • Participate in coordination meetings, workshops, and policy dialogues.

Technical Oversight and Quality Assurance

  • Oversee development and review of training modules and accessible digital content.

  • Ensure training aligns with national TVET curricula and inclusive education standards.

  • Supervise teacher training, ToTs, and master trainer sessions.

  • Ensure assistive technologies provided are appropriate and functional.

Monitoring, Evaluation, and Reporting

  • Coordinate routine monitoring of project activities and outputs.

  • Ensure timely collection and review of monitoring reports.

  • Support baseline, midline, and endline evaluations.

  • Prepare narrative reports for donors and partners.

  • Assist in project evaluation and audit processes.

Financial and Administrative Coordination

  • Track project expenditures with the Finance team.

  • Ensure timely submission of procurement requests and budgets.

  • Monitor cost-effectiveness and resource use.

  • Support donor compliance and accountability requirements.

Risk Management and Problem Solving

  • Identify and mitigate implementation risks.

  • Resolve operational challenges in a timely manner.

  • Maintain strong communication within the project team.

Knowledge Management and Sustainability

  • Promote institutional learning within RATA and partner institutions.

  • Support sustainability strategies, including integration of AT content into CPD programs and RTB platforms.

  • Document best practices, lessons learned, and success stories.

Deliverables

  • Approved annual and quarterly work plans

  • Timely donor and internal narrative reports

  • Coordinated and documented training and awareness campaigns

  • Functional collaboration with RTB and TVET schools

  • Contribution to baseline, final evaluation, and audit reports

  • Documented lessons learned and best practices

Required Qualifications and Experience

  • Bachelor‚Äôs degree in Education, Project Management, Inclusive and Special Needs Education, Disability Studies, ICT for Development, or a related field (Master‚Äôs is an advantage).

  • 3‚Äì5 years of progressive experience coordinating education, inclusion, ICT, or development projects.

  • Experience working with government institutions, preferably in education or TVET.

  • Experience in disability inclusion, inclusive education, or assistive technology projects is highly desirable.

  • Proven experience managing donor-funded projects.

Competencies and Skills

  • Strong project coordination and organizational skills

  • Excellent stakeholder engagement and communication abilities

  • Strong report writing and documentation skills

  • Knowledge of inclusive education and disability frameworks

  • Ability to manage multiple activities and meet deadlines

  • Strong problem-solving and leadership skills

  • Proficiency in English; knowledge of Kinyarwanda is required

How to Apply

Submit the following by email to hr@rata.rw:

  • Detailed CV including three professional references (at least one from a previous employer)

  • Certified copies of academic degrees and certificates

  • Motivation letter addressed to the Executive Director

Email Subject: Project Coordinator ‚Äì RATA 2025

Additional Information:

  • This is a full-time position for a 12-month project with potential extension subject to funding.

  • The role requires regular travel to TVET institutions across Rwanda.

  • Adherence to RATA‚Äôs safeguarding, child protection, disability inclusion, and anti-corruption policies is mandatory.

title: Supply Chain Officer at RwandAir Ltd
description:
Supply Chain Officer-RwandAir Ltd

Location: Kigali International Airport (KIA), Rwanda
Department: Technical
Reports To: Manager, Materials Planning & Rotable Management
Job Type: Full-time
Deadline: 13 January 2026

Job Overview

RwandAir Ltd, the national flag carrier airline of Rwanda, operates domestic and international services across Africa, Europe, and the Middle East from its hub at Kigali International Airport. As part of its expansion strategy, RwandAir is seeking a qualified and motivated Supply Chain Officer ‚Äì AOG to support aircraft availability and airworthiness.

The role focuses on Aircraft on Ground (AOG) operations, ensuring timely availability of aircraft parts and materials, minimizing operational disruptions, and supporting rapid recovery of grounded aircraft in collaboration with the Maintenance Control Center (MCC).

Key Responsibilities

AOG & Operational Support

  • Support a 24/7 AOG operation to ensure rapid response to aircraft grounding events.

  • Ensure availability of spares, materials, and services to clear deferred defects (including cabin and IFE) within the shortest possible time.

  • Act as the focal point for AOG spares coordination and inquiries from internal teams and partner airlines.

  • Monitor all AOG and MEL-related shipments from dispatch to delivery, ensuring correct routing and timely arrival.

  • Coordinate return of loaned and exchanged components within agreed timelines to minimize costs.

  • Monitor recurrent AOG events and propose preventive measures to reduce future occurrences.

  • Maintain accurate and up-to-date AOG/MEL trackers and ensure TRAX eMRO is promptly updated.

  • Ensure suppliers provide correct documentation prior to shipment to avoid receiving discrepancies.

  • Verify availability of parts (NHA/NLA) internally before sourcing externally.

Supply Chain & Repair Management

  • Progress overdue repair orders and expedite priority components.

  • Raise and manage repair and service orders.

  • Monitor unserviceable inventory and initiate actions to expedite release.

  • Update TRAX eMRO with repair capabilities, pricing, and supplier information.

  • Review parts removed during maintenance for exchange, return, or further action.

  • Review and approve scrap notes and workflow order approvals.

  • Ensure all received parts are properly certified and documentation archived.

  • Explore open-market solutions for advance exchanges and loan components when required.

Leadership & Talent Development

  • Train and support staff to ensure effective succession planning.

  • Contribute to national talent development by coaching and mentoring RwandAir staff.

  • Support staff development in line with operational and business requirements.

Safety, Data Protection & Compliance

  • Ensure compliance with Safety Management System (SMS), quality, security, and environmental policies.

  • Report and follow up on incidents, hazards, and near misses.

  • Ensure all data handling complies with RwandAir‚Äôs data protection and confidentiality policies.

  • Promote environmental responsibility in supply chain and operational decision-making.

Qualifications & Experience

Essential

  • Diploma in Aircraft Maintenance, Trade, Supply Chain Management, or vocational aircraft maintenance qualification,
    OR Bachelor‚Äôs degree (BEng, BSc) in Aircraft Engineering or related field with at least 3 years‚Äô experience in supply chain.

  • Working knowledge of aircraft spares purchasing and materials management.

  • Knowledge of international procurement, customs clearance, and logistics processes.

  • Completion of Hazardous Materials training.

  • Familiarity with OEM and regulatory documentation systems.

  • Strong analytical, organizational, and communication skills.

  • Ability to manage large datasets and ensure data accuracy.

  • Fluency in English (French or Kinyarwanda is an added advantage).

Preferred

  • Experience with aircraft maintenance and engineering systems such as TRAX or AMOS.

  • Previous involvement in aircraft maintenance activities.

How to Apply

Interested candidates should submit the following documents in PDF format only:

  • Application letter addressed to the Chief HR & Administration Officer

  • Recent Curriculum Vitae (CV)

  • Notarized copies of degree/diploma certificates

  • Relevant professional certificates

  • Copies of academic papers

  • Copy of Passport or National ID

  • Contact details of three referees

title: PLATFORM & AI DATA ENGINEERS OFFICERS (2 POSITIONS) at Clinton Health Access Initiative (CHAI) ‚Äì Rwanda
description:
JOB VACANCY: PLATFORM & AI DATA ENGINEERS OFFICERS (2 POSITIONS)

Organization: Clinton Health Access Initiative (CHAI) ‚Äì Rwanda

Program: Digital Health
Duty Station: Kigali, Rwanda
Employment Type: Full-Time (Paid)
Start Date: Immediate

About CHAI

The Clinton Health Access Initiative, Inc. (CHAI) is a global health organization committed to saving lives and reducing the burden of disease in low- and middle-income countries. CHAI partners with governments and the private sector to strengthen health systems and ensure sustainable, high-quality healthcare delivery.

In Rwanda, CHAI supports the Government‚Äôs goal of achieving Universal Health Coverage (UHC) through health system strengthening initiatives aligned with the Health Sector Strategic Plan. CHAI works closely with the Ministry of Health (MoH), Rwanda Social Security Board (RSSB), and other national stakeholders to improve data-driven decision-making, service delivery, and digital health systems.

Position Overview

CHAI Rwanda is seeking two (2) Platform & AI Data Engineers Officers to support the Ministry of Health‚Äôs National Health Intelligence Center (NHIC). The positions will focus on designing, deploying, and maintaining scalable, secure, and reliable data and AI platform infrastructure that supports national health analytics, artificial intelligence, and digital health systems.

The engineers will play a critical role in building and operating national data platforms, MLOps systems, and DevOps pipelines that enable data scientists, AI engineers, and analysts to safely and efficiently deploy AI solutions for public health and clinical use.

The successful candidates will be seconded to NHIC and report functionally to the CHAI Digital Health Program Manager while working closely with MoH and NHIC technical teams.

Key Responsibilities

1. National AI & Platform Infrastructure Engineering

  • Design, build, and operate scalable, secure AI and data platform infrastructure (cloud, hybrid, and/or on-premises).

  • Implement Infrastructure-as-Code (IaC) and automated environment provisioning.

  • Ensure separation of research, staging, and regulated production environments.

  • Implement disaster recovery, backup, failover, and business continuity mechanisms.

2. MLOps & AI Lifecycle Operations

  • Operate end-to-end MLOps platforms supporting model training, validation, deployment, rollback, and retirement.

  • Enforce model versioning, reproducibility, and audit trails.

  • Implement model performance monitoring, data drift detection, and automated retraining workflows.

  • Support real-time and batch AI inference integrated into national health systems.

3. Data Platforms, Pipelines & Feature Infrastructure

  • Design and manage large-scale data platforms for structured and unstructured health data.

  • Build and maintain batch and streaming data pipelines.

  • Support AI training pipelines, feature engineering, and feature stores.

  • Ensure dataset versioning, lineage tracking, and regulatory traceability.

4. Security, Reliability & Compliance

  • Implement access controls, encryption, audit logging, and inference traceability.

  • Ensure compliance with national data protection, health data governance, and cybersecurity regulations.

  • Implement fail-safe mechanisms to protect continuity of clinical services.

  • Conduct platform hardening, vulnerability assessments, and threat monitoring.

5. CI/CD, GitOps & Automation

  • Design and maintain secure CI/CD and GitOps pipelines for data platforms and AI services.

  • Implement automated testing, security scanning, and controlled production releases.

  • Ensure all deployments follow auditable pipelines and governance standards.

6. Performance, Cost & Resource Governance

  • Manage compute infrastructure including GPU clusters and distributed training environments.

  • Implement resource quotas, workload separation, and cost monitoring.

  • Optimize compute utilization, platform performance, and cost efficiency.

7. Interoperability & System Integration

  • Enable AI and data integration with EMRs, HMIS, surveillance, laboratory, and registry systems.

  • Support standards-based real-time and batch data exchange within national workflows.

8. Collaboration & Enablement

  • Provide secure AI development environments for engineers, data scientists, and researchers.

  • Work closely with NHIC, MoH digital health teams, and CHAI technical staff.

  • Support technical proposals, system design reviews, and national AI deployments.

9. Documentation & Continuous Improvement

  • Maintain detailed documentation of platform architecture, pipelines, and security controls.

  • Assess emerging technologies to improve scalability, reliability, and AI operational safety.

Required Qualifications

Education

  • Bachelor‚Äôs degree or Diploma in Computer Science, Information Systems, Engineering, or a related field (or equivalent experience).

Experience & Skills

  • Minimum of 4 years of experience in software engineering, platform engineering, or DevOps.

  • Experience with Docker, Kubernetes, GitOps, and Infrastructure-as-Code tools (Terraform, Ansible).

  • Proficiency in SQL and relational databases (e.g., PostgreSQL).

  • Understanding of networking, monitoring, and security best practices.

  • Strong analytical and problem-solving skills.

  • Ability to work collaboratively with multidisciplinary teams.

  • Strong written and verbal communication skills.

  • Commitment to data quality and accuracy.

Nice-to-Have

  • Experience with ETL tools (Apache NiFi, Airflow, Talend).

  • Exposure to cloud platforms (AWS, Google Cloud, Azure).

  • Familiarity with big data frameworks (Spark, Kafka, Hadoop).

  • Experience with non-relational databases (MongoDB).

  • Knowledge of data warehousing solutions (BigQuery, Snowflake, Redshift).

  • Experience supporting on-premises data environments.

How to Apply

Interested candidates should submit:

  • A letter of interest (maximum 1 page)

  • Curriculum Vitae (CV) (maximum 3 pages)

  • Names of three professional referees
