üìå Deadline: January 23rd, 2026
üìå Only shortlisted candidates will be contacted.

title: Handyman at Solid'Africa
description:
Job Advertisement 

ABOUT SOLID‚ÄôAFRICA

Operating in Rwanda since 2010, Solid‚ÄôAfrica is a pioneering social enterprise dedicated to combating nutrition insecurity in Rwanda and beyond. With a mission to ensure universal access to adequate and appropriate nutrition. Solid‚ÄôAfrica delivers a comprehensive nutrition access program that includes the Gemura Feeding Program, which supplies nutritious meals to hospital patients and school children; the Sustainable Agriculture Program, which supports local farmers and strengthens the food supply chain; and the Nutrition Education Program, which promotes healthy dietary choices through education and awareness. 

Through its Community Benefit Company (CBC), Solid‚ÄôAfrica also generates income to subsidize its non-profit initiatives, ensuring financial sustainability. Additionally, Solid‚ÄôAfrica‚Äôs Institute of Culinary Arts and Nutrition (ICAN) provides specialized training that blends nutrition science and culinary arts to empower hospitality professionals. By leveraging strategic collaborations, adopting a holistic Farm-to-plate model, and focusing on sustainable practices, Solid‚ÄôAfrica aims to transform the nutrition landscape, making healthy meals universally accessible in the communities it serves. 

Solid‚ÄôAfrica is seeking experienced candidates for the positions listed below, to be based at Remera Rukoma location


POSITIONS OVERVIEW

Position

Number of Staff

Responsibilities

Requirements 

Handyman 

1

The Handyman is responsible for assisting in routine maintenance, minor repairs, and general upkeep of the catering facility. This role supports the maintenance team in ensuring that kitchen equipment, plumbing, electrical systems, and infrastructure remain in optimal working condition. The Handyman also helps with daily maintenance tasks, preventive maintenance checks, and emergency repairs as required.

 

Responsibilities 

  • Assist in carrying out minor electrical, plumbing, carpentry, and mechanical repairs 

  • Support routine maintenance of kitchen appliances, gas installations, HVAC systems, water filtration systems, and other utilities.

  • Help with painting, sealing leaks, fixing door handles, locks, hinges, and other structural elements.

  • Identify potential maintenance issues and report them to the Repairs & Maintenance Manager.

  • Assist in cleaning and servicing kitchen machinery and equipment under the supervision of the maintenance team.

  • Support the installation, relocation, or removal of appliances, furniture, and fixtures.

  • Keep maintenance areas, tools, and equipment organized and in good working order.

  • Help monitor water, gas, and electricity consumption, reporting irregularities.

  • Assist in scheduled preventive maintenance tasks to avoid breakdowns.

  • Be on standby for emergency repairs, such as fixing leaks, unclogging drains, replacing bulbs, and minor electrical fixes.

  • Respond to urgent repair requests in a timely and efficient manner.

Qualifications and experience required

  • Certificate/Diploma in a relevant technical field (electrical, plumbing, or general maintenance) is an advantage.

  • 2+ years of experience in a similar role, preferably in a hotel, catering facility, or large commercial kitchen.

  • Basic knowledge of electrical, plumbing, carpentry, and mechanical repairs.

  • Experience working with kitchen equipment and utilities is an added advantage.

  • Ability to follow instructions, work independently, and handle multiple maintenance tasks.

  • Strong problem-solving skills and attention to detail.

  • Hands-on maintenance skills with knowledge of basic repair techniques.

  • Reliability and strong work ethic to ensure quick response to maintenance needs.

  • Physical stamina to handle tasks requiring lifting, bending, and working in tight spaces.

APPLICATION GUIDELINES: Interested and qualified candidates should submit a 1page Cover letter, and updated CV (maximum three pages) and names, title and contacts of three professional referees, to include the most recent or current employer/supervisor (all in/as one document) - via email only to: hr@solidafrica.org with the POSITION applied for clearly indicated in the subject line. The deadline for submission of applications is December 11th, 2025, at 16:00hrs.
Only shortlisted candidates will be contacted.
Solid‚ÄôAfrica is an Equal Opportunity Employer offering employment without regard to race, color, religion, gender, age, national origin, physical disability.

title: Program Officer (2 Positions) at Digital Opportunity Trust (DOT)
description:
Call for Applications: Program Officer (2 Positions)

Location: Kigali, Rwanda
Application Deadline: Sunday, 11th January 2026, 05:00 PM GMT+2

Position: Program Officer
Reports to: Program Manager
Type: Full-time, Term Contract
Salary: Up to 700,000 RWF (based on experience)
Start Date: Immediate

About Digital Opportunity Trust (DOT)

Digital Opportunity Trust (DOT) is an international non-profit organization headquartered in Ottawa, Canada. For over 23 years, DOT has empowered young women and men across Africa and the Middle East with digital skills, leadership competencies, climate action awareness, and opportunities to participate in an inclusive digital economy.

Since 2010, DOT Rwanda has supported over 120,000 young people through digital literacy programs, 21st-century skills development, and entrepreneurship training. DOT works closely with government, higher learning institutions, civil society, and private sector partners to strengthen digital capacity and youth leadership across urban and rural communities.

About The RISE Program

The Resilience in Secondary Education (RISE) program targets 1.1 million out-of-school youth, providing technology-enabled, accredited secondary education. Led by UNICEF, in collaboration with the Ministry of Education and Mastercard Foundation, the RISE consortium includes DOT Rwanda, Carnegie Mellon University (CMU), and implementing partners such as the Imbuto Foundation, CRS, and YWCA.

DOT Rwanda leads the Facilitator Development Pathway, equipping recent graduates with the digital and facilitation skills required to serve as RISE Facilitators. DOT designs the competency framework and provides continuous coaching and quality assurance to ensure facilitators effectively guide youth through accredited, technology-enabled secondary education pathways.

Position Overview

The Program Officer serves as the primary link between central management and field activities, ensuring operational coherence of the facilitator support system. The role includes managing a cluster of District-based Quality Assurance Technicians (QATs) and supporting the rollout of the blended facilitator training model.

Key Responsibilities

  • Team Management: Coach, mentor, and supervise QATs within assigned district clusters to ensure high-quality support to learning sites.

  • Training Delivery: Lead and support delivery of the 4-phase blended facilitator training model, including in-person district onboarding and Practical ‚ÄúDemo Days.‚Äù

  • Quality Oversight: Conduct field visits to monitor QAT-facilitator interactions, identifying and resolving gaps in real-time.

  • Operational Coordination: Manage logistics for district-level delivery and maintain real-time digital reporting for accountability.

  • Stakeholder Collaboration: Work closely with District and Sector Education Officers to ensure alignment with local government priorities.

Required Qualifications

  • Age: 21‚Äì35 years

  • Resident of Rwanda and legally able to work in the country

  • Bachelor‚Äôs degree or professional equivalent in Computer Science, ICT, Education Technology, or related fields

  • Experience in large-scale program implementation, youth facilitation, and field-based mentoring

  • High speed of execution, excellent field coordination, and advanced digital reporting skills

  • Fluency in Kinyarwanda and English

  • Successful completion of DOT‚Äôs Digital Pre-Screening

  • Ability to provide constructive, evidence-based feedback

What DOT Offers

  • Competitive salary within the RISE program budget

  • Communication and transport allowances for field-related travel

title: Laboratory Technician at Wellspring Academy
description:
JOB ADVERTISEMENT

Date: January 16, 2026

Position: Laboratory Technician

Location: Wellspring Academy, Nyarutarama
2 KG 270 St, Kigali, Rwanda

About Wellspring Academy

Wellspring Academy is a Christian international school guided by a vision to raise a new generation of servant leaders who will bless Rwanda and represent the best of Rwanda to the world. Our mission is to educate and equip students to become highly skilled, Godly leaders and agents of community transformation.

Would you be interested in joining such a community?

Why Join Wellspring Academy?

Wellspring Academy is a destination for curious minds where academic excellence, Godly character, and servant leadership are nurtured through a Christ-centered curriculum.

Our team members are not only subject experts‚Äîthey are mentors, role models, and spiritual leaders committed to shaping lives for God‚Äôs glory.

Key Responsibilities

The Laboratory Technician will be responsible for supporting effective science teaching and learning through the management and coordination of laboratory activities.

Core Duties

  • Liaise with academic staff to plan laboratory timetables, equipment use, and work plans

  • Prepare and conduct trial experiments prior to lessons and demonstrate practical techniques to students

  • Set up laboratory equipment and materials, including microscopes and scientific instruments

  • Maintain, calibrate, and repair laboratory equipment as required

  • Ensure proper cleaning, safe storage, and handling of chemicals and laboratory materials

  • Manage inventory and stock levels of laboratory equipment and chemicals

  • Enforce health and safety regulations and ensure compliance at all times

  • Keep accurate records of experiments, student practical work, and laboratory usage

  • Catalog and organize experimental records for accessibility

  • Support teachers during laboratory sessions with technical guidance

  • Provide individual student support for practical research and experimental learning

  • Coordinate laboratory activities to optimize resource utilization

Pastoral & School Responsibilities

  • Undertake pastoral duties, including acting as a form tutor where assigned

  • Support students academically and personally in alignment with Christian values

  • Prepare students for examinations and assessments

  • Manage student behavior in laboratory and school environments

  • Participate in extracurricular activities such as science fairs, school events, and outings

  • Attend staff meetings, parent engagements, and school-wide training sessions

  • Engage in continuous professional development and in-service training

  • Perform other duties within the scope of the role as assigned

Reporting Line:
The Laboratory Technician will report directly to the Deputy Principal ‚Äì Secondary Section.

Qualifications & Experience

Required Qualifications

  • Bachelor‚Äôs degree or higher in Education Science with specialization in:

    • Biology

    • Chemistry

    • Physics

    • General Science

Experience & Skills

  • Minimum of 2 years‚Äô experience in a school laboratory environment

  • Experience in an international school is a strong advantage

  • Proven experience managing practical science lessons and experiments

  • Strong knowledge of laboratory equipment, materials, and safety procedures

  • Excellent organizational, communication, and interpersonal skills

  • Ability to work collaboratively in a multicultural school environment

  • Flexibility and adaptability to meet evolving school needs

Additional Qualifications (Advantageous)

  • Certifications in laboratory safety or educational pedagogy

Professional Characteristics

  • Demonstrates a Christ-centered worldview, integrity, and servant leadership

  • Passionate about science education and hands-on laboratory learning

  • Reflective, adaptable, and committed to continuous professional growth

  • Builds respectful relationships with students, staff, and parents

  • Values safety, professionalism, and a nurturing learning environment

Contract Type & Duration

  • Full-time position

  • One-year contract including a three-month probationary period

  • Open-ended contract upon successful completion

What We Offer

  • A Christ-centered, nurturing, and professional work environment

  • Opportunity to grow and serve in a purpose-driven community

  • Competitive compensation package based on experience and qualifications

How to Apply

Interested candidates are encouraged to apply by January 23, 2026 using the link below:

üìå Applications will be reviewed on a rolling basis. Interviews will continue until the position is filled. Early applications are strongly encouraged.

A. JOB PURPOSE:

The Manager mainly helps the Cooperative to meet its vision, mission and objective in general, and in particularly its customer acquisition and revenue growth targets by keeping the Cooperative competitive. Operation management

Compliances, risk management and corporate governance

Reports directly to the ‚ÄúPresident of the Board of Directors‚Äù of the Cooperative (Conseil administration)

title: Revenue Accountant at Akagera Management Company
description:
AKAGERA NATIONAL PARK _JOB VACANCY ANNOUNCEMENT

Akagera Management Company Ltd (AMC Ltd) is a public‚Äìprivate partnership between African Parks Network and the Rwanda Development Board (RDB), mandated to manage Akagera National Park.

AMC Ltd is seeking to recruit a qualified, motivated, and results-oriented Rwandan professional to fill the following position:

Job Title: Revenue Accountant

Reporting to: Finance Manager
Duty Station: Akagera National Park

Job Purpose

The Revenue Accountant is responsible for the accurate recording, reconciliation, analysis, and reporting of all company revenue. The role ensures that revenue is recognized in compliance with applicable accounting standards, internal controls, and statutory requirements, while supporting audits, budgeting, and financial decision-making.

Key Duties and Responsibilities

  • Record and post all revenue transactions in the accounting system (Serenic Navigator) in accordance with the approved chart of accounts

  • Ensure revenue recognition complies with applicable accounting standards

  • Prepare monthly, quarterly, and annual revenue reports

  • Reconcile revenue accounts with billing, sales, and cash receipts

  • Reconcile RRA Back-Office invoices with AMC ledger records

  • Review contracts and agreements to determine appropriate revenue treatment

  • Monitor deferred and accrued revenue balances

  • Support internal and external audits by providing revenue-related documentation

  • Support preparation of tax annexures, VAT reconciliations, and statutory tax declarations related to revenue

  • Investigate and resolve revenue discrepancies or variances

  • Collaborate with Commercial and Finance teams to ensure accurate invoicing

  • Assist in budgeting, forecasting, and revenue analysis

  • Verify that all sales invoices are supported by proof of payment and properly reflected in AMC accounts

Minimum Qualifications and Experience

Education & Professional Qualifications

  • Bachelor‚Äôs degree in Accounting, Finance, or a related field

  • Professional qualification: CPA (Advanced Level) or ACCA (mandatory)

  • Strong knowledge of tax and revenue-related regulations

Experience

  • Minimum of 2‚Äì5 years‚Äô experience in accounting or finance

  • Proven experience in revenue accounting, reconciliations, and financial reporting

  • Experience working in a multi-currency environment is an added advantage

Skills and Competencies

  • Strong understanding of IFRS revenue recognition principles

  • High level of accuracy and attention to detail

  • Advanced proficiency in Microsoft Excel

  • Experience with accounting systems (Serenic Navigator is an added advantage)

  • Strong analytical and problem-solving skills

  • Ability to work under pressure and meet strict deadlines

  • High level of integrity, professionalism, and confidentiality

  • Good communication and interpersonal skills

  • Fluency in English and Kinyarwanda

  • Willingness to live and work in a remote or rural setting

  • Strong alignment with African Parks values

Added Advantage

  • Born and currently living near Akagera National Park

How to Apply

Interested candidates should submit their application no later than 15th January 2026 to:

üìß amc.recruit@africanparks.org

Application Requirements

Applications must be submitted in one single PDF document and include:

  • Application cover letter addressed to the Park Manager / CEO, stating where you heard about the position and why you should be considered

  • Detailed Curriculum Vitae (CV)

  • Copies of academic and professional certificates

  • Names, addresses, and telephone numbers of three (3) referees

üìå File naming format:
Full Name ‚Äì Revenue Accountant ‚Äì 2026

Important Notes

  • Applications that do not meet the stated criteria will not be considered

  • Only shortlisted candidates will be contacted

title: Chief Accountant
description:
VACANCY ANNOUNCEMENT

Background

ACB Plc is a Christian Micro Finance Institution that started its operations in August 2006. It is licensed by the National Bank of Rwanda (BNR). Our vision is to be a leading Christian financial institution that contributes to holistic and sustainable development. Our mission is to bring holistic transformation into the community through quality financial services. Our values are quality service, transparency, integrity and accountability. We are committed to taking financial services closer to the people.

AMASEZERANO Community Banking (ACB) Plc is looking for qualified, competent, committed, proactiveand self-motivated individual to occupy the following positions.

 

CHIEF ACCOUNTANT

Department: Finance

Reporting to: Head of Finance

Number of positions: 1

Job summary

To manage and control the day-to-day accounting operations of the bank, ensuring accurate financial records, timely financial reporting, strong internal controls, and full compliance with Rwandan laws, tax regulations, and National Bank of Rwanda (NBR) requirements, while supporting the Head of Finance in strategic financial management.

I. KEY ROLES AND RESPONSIBILITIES 

  • Prepare monthly, quarterly, and annual financial statements in accordance with IFRS/IFRS for SMEs and internal reporting requirements.

  • Maintain complete, accurate, and up-to-date books of accounts and ensure proper documentation of all financial transactions.

  • Oversee general ledger management, bank reconciliations, cash and mobile money reconciliations.

  • Ensure accurate accounting for loan disbursements, repayments, interest accruals, penalties, provisions, write-offs, and recoveries.

  • Prepare regulatory and statutory financial reports as required by the National Bank of Rwanda and other regulatory authorities.

  • Ensure full compliance with Rwanda tax laws (PAYE, VAT, Withholding Tax, and Corporate Income Tax) and timely submission of all tax returns.

  • Monitor budget performance and prepare variance analysis with recommendations for management.

  • Maintain and strengthen internal controls over financial operations and ensure segregation of duties.

  • Coordinate internal and external audits and prepare audit schedules; follow up on audit recommendations.

  • Supervise, mentor, and evaluate accounting staff and ensure their continuous professional development.

  • Ensure proper maintenance of the fixed assets register and periodic physical verification of assets.

  • Manage accounts payable and accounts receivable, ensuring timely payments and collections.

  • Support treasury operations including daily liquidity monitoring and bank relationship management.

  • Perform any other duties assigned by the supervisor.

II. QUALIFICATIONS, SKILLS & EXPERIENCE

  • Bachelor‚Äôs degree in Accounting, Finance, Business Administration, or a related field. Possessing CPA qualificationis an added value.

  • Strong knowledge of IFRS/IFRS for SMEs and financial institution accounting.

  • Minimum 3 years relevant working experience in accounting field.

  • Hands-on experience in statutory audits, tax filings, and regulatory reporting.

  • Experience working with accounting software and core banking systems.

  • Strong analytical and problem-solving skills.

  • High level of integrity, ethics, and confidentiality.

  • Excellent leadership, supervisory, and communication skills.

  • Strong attention to detail and accuracy.

  • Ability to meet strict deadlines and work under pressure.

  • Advanced proficiency in MS Excel and financial reporting tools.

How to apply

The vacancies are open from 4th to 19th December 2025. The interested candidates should submit their application documents (Application letter, updated CV, Academic certificates, ID copy, current criminal record certificate and original church recommendation letter signed by your church Pastor) to the ACB Plc via company email amasezerano@acb.rw, not later than 19th December 2025 (05:00 pm).

Note: Only shortlisted candidates will be contacted for the written and oral tests. If you do not hear from us 2 weeks from the closing date, consider your application unsuccessful.

Eraste NSENGIYUMVA

Managing Director

description:

Location: Kigali, Rwanda

Job Type: Full-Time

About Ecofleet Solutions Ltd

Ecofleet Solutions Ltd is a government-owned company driving the modernization of public transport in Rwanda, beginning with operations in Kigali. We manage and operate the city‚Äôs public bus fleet, establish service standards and operational SLAs, and shape the wider urban transport ecosystem.

Ecofleet is committed to delivering a smart, efficient, and environmentally sustainable transport system. Guided by global best practices, data-driven operations, and modern technology, our vision includes transitioning to electric mobility, digital ticketing systems, smart depots, and green infrastructure‚Äîpositioning Kigali as a leading example of eco-friendly urban transport in Africa.

1. Role Summary

The Accountant supports the Finance Department by maintaining accurate financial records, processing daily transactions, and contributing to financial reporting, reconciliation, and compliance. Under the supervision of the Senior Accountant, the role ensures strong internal controls and efficient financial operations in alignment with Ecofleet‚Äôs strategic goals.

e) Other Duties

  • Support continuous improvement of finance processes and systems.

4. Indicators of Success

  • Timely and accurate posting of financial transactions and reconciliations.

External

6. Core Competencies & Skills

  • Strong analytical, documentation, and problem-solving abilities.

  • Ability to work under pressure and meet strict deadlines.

7. Values & Cultural Fit

8. Qualifications & Experience

Minimum Requirements

Preferred

JOB ANNOUNCEMENT

Application Deadline: 15th January 2026 at 5:00 PM

About Ubumwe SACCO Gakenke (USG)

Ubumwe SACCO Gakenke (USG) is the Head Office of all Umurenge SACCOs in Gakenke District, merged in August 2025. USG is duly registered under RCA Certificate No. RGDG013305 and licensed by the National Bank of Rwanda (BNR).

In accordance with Law N¬∫ 072/2021 of 05/11/2021 governing Deposit-Taking Microfinance Institutions, USG is authorized to conduct microfinance activities in the Republic of Rwanda.

USG invites qualified, committed, customer-oriented, and competent professionals to apply for the position of Lawyer (Legal Advisor).

Role Summary

The Legal Advisor plays a critical role in safeguarding the SACCO from legal, regulatory, and compliance risks, ensuring that all operations adhere to applicable laws, regulations, and best practices in the microfinance and cooperative sector.

Key Duties and Responsibilities

1. Legal Advisory & Compliance

  • Provide timely legal advice to the Board, Management, and departments.

  • Ensure compliance with cooperative laws, data protection regulations, employment laws, and other applicable legislation.

2. Policy and Document Management

  • Review, develop, and update internal policies, procedures, bylaws, and governance documents in line with legal requirements and industry best practices.

3. Contract Management

  • Draft, review, negotiate, and manage contracts, service agreements, leases, and Memoranda of Understanding (MOUs).

  • Maintain a secure and organized registry of all legal documents.

4. Litigation and Dispute Resolution

  • Handle all legal proceedings involving the SACCO.

title: How to Find Jobs in Rwanda in 2025 ‚Äì Step-by-Step Guide
description:
How to Find Jobs in Rwanda in 2025 ‚Äì Step-by-Step Guide

Introduction

Finding a job in Rwanda has become more competitive in recent years due to the growing number of graduates and job seekers. However, with the right strategy, tools, and information, it is still possible to secure a good job in 2025.

This guide explains step by step how to find jobs in Rwanda, where to search, how to apply correctly, and how to avoid common mistakes.

Understand the Rwanda Job Market

Before applying for jobs, it is important to understand where opportunities exist.

High-Demand Sectors in Rwanda

  • NGOs & Development Organizations

  • Banking & Finance

  • Education

  • Health

  • Sales & Marketing

  • Hospitality & Tourism

  • IT & Digital Skills

Most jobs are concentrated in Kigali, but other cities like Huye, Musanze, Rubavu, and Nyagatare also offer opportunities.

Where to Find Jobs in Rwanda

1Ô∏è‚É£ Online Job Websites

Online job platforms are the fastest and most reliable way to find jobs.

Examples:

  • RwandaJobHub

  • Company websites

  • NGO websites

üëâ Tip: Always apply through trusted platforms that post verified jobs.

2Ô∏è‚É£ Company Career Pages

Many companies advertise jobs only on their own websites.

Examples:

  • Banks

  • Telecom companies

  • NGOs

  • Private institutions

Check their ‚ÄúCareers‚Äù or ‚ÄúVacancies‚Äù pages regularly.

3Ô∏è‚É£ Social Media (WhatsApp & Facebook)

WhatsApp and Facebook are very popular in Rwanda for job sharing.

Best practices:

  • Join trusted job groups like Rwanda Job Hub group: https://chat.whatsapp.com/Ky7m3B0M5Gd3saO58Rb1tI

  • Avoid groups that ask for money

  • Always verify job sources

4Ô∏è‚É£ Networking

Networking is very powerful in Rwanda.

You can:

  • Attend career events

  • Talk to friends and colleagues

  • Ask professionals for guidance

Sometimes jobs are filled before being advertised.

How to Apply for Jobs in Rwanda Correctly

-Prepare a Professional CV

Your CV should:

  • Be 1‚Äì2 pages

  • Include clear work experience

  • Be updated

  • Have correct contact details

-Avoid spelling and grammar mistakes.

-Write a Strong Cover Letter

A good cover letter:

  • Is specific to the job

  • Shows why you are suitable

  • Is short and clear (1 page)

-Never send the same cover letter to all jobs.

Apply Before the Deadline

Late applications are usually rejected automatically.

üëâ Apply at least 2‚Äì3 days before the deadline.

Common Mistakes Job Seekers Make in Rwanda

‚ùå Applying without reading job requirements
‚ùå Using the same CV for all jobs
‚ùå Paying money to ‚Äújob agents‚Äù
‚ùå Ignoring deadlines
‚ùå Applying to fake jobs

‚ö†Ô∏è Important: Legitimate employers in Rwanda do NOT ask for payment.

How to Increase Your Chances of Getting a Job

‚úî Apply consistently (at least 5‚Äì10 jobs per week)
‚úî Improve your skills (short courses help)
‚úî Follow application instructions carefully
‚úî Prepare for interviews
‚úî Stay positive and patient

Final Advice

Finding a job in Rwanda takes time, but with the right approach, success is possible. Use trusted job platforms, prepare quality applications, and stay consistent.

Find Latest Job Vacancies in Rwanda

üîé Browse verified and updated job opportunities here:
üëâ https://www.rwandajobhub.rw

üëâJoin our WhatsApp group: https://chat.whatsapp.com/Ky7m3B0M5Gd3saO58Rb1tI

title: Plumber at Solid'Africa
description:
Job Advertisement 

ABOUT SOLID‚ÄôAFRICA

Operating in Rwanda since 2010, Solid‚ÄôAfrica is a pioneering social enterprise dedicated to combating nutrition insecurity in Rwanda and beyond. With a mission to ensure universal access to adequate and appropriate nutrition. Solid‚ÄôAfrica delivers a comprehensive nutrition access program that includes the Gemura Feeding Program, which supplies nutritious meals to hospital patients and school children; the Sustainable Agriculture Program, which supports local farmers and strengthens the food supply chain; and the Nutrition Education Program, which promotes healthy dietary choices through education and awareness. 

Through its Community Benefit Company (CBC), Solid‚ÄôAfrica also generates income to subsidize its non-profit initiatives, ensuring financial sustainability. Additionally, Solid‚ÄôAfrica‚Äôs Institute of Culinary Arts and Nutrition (ICAN) provides specialized training that blends nutrition science and culinary arts to empower hospitality professionals. By leveraging strategic collaborations, adopting a holistic Farm-to-plate model, and focusing on sustainable practices, Solid‚ÄôAfrica aims to transform the nutrition landscape, making healthy meals universally accessible in the communities it serves. 

Solid‚ÄôAfrica is seeking experienced candidates for the positions listed below, to be based at Remera Rukoma location


POSITIONS OVERVIEW

Position

Number of Staff

Responsibilities

Requirements 

Plumber 

1

The Plumber will support SolidAfrica‚Äôs food industry and kitchen facilities by ensuring proper installation, maintenance, and repair of all plumbing systems, including water supply lines, drainage networks, kitchen equipment connections, and preventive maintenance to guarantee smooth, hygienic, and safe kitchen operations.

 

Responsibilities 

 

  • Maintenance & Repair

  • Repair or replace faulty fixtures such as pumps, heaters, WCs, and traps.

B. Installation & Upgrades

  • Install new plumbing systems and kitchen equipment connections.

C.Preventive Maintenance

  • Develop and implement preventive maintenance schedules.

  • Conduct routine inspections to detect risks early.

D.Compliance & Standards

  • Ensure all plumbing works meet hygiene and safety standards for food-processing environments.

E. Coordination & Reporting

  • Respond quickly to plumbing emergencies such as leaks, blockages, or water supply failures.

title: Malaria and Community Health Technical Officer
description:
Overview

Reaching Impact, Saturation, and Epidemic Control (RISE) Project support the Ministry of Health (MOH) in responding to Global Health Security (GHS) emergencies and strengthening malaria prevention and control interventions. This is achieved through technical assistance, service delivery support, research, and cross-cutting health systems strengthening to reduce malaria mortality and incidence in Rwanda, with a focus on improving the availability, quality, and utilization of malaria services.

Reporting to the Senior Malaria Technical Officer, the Malaria and Community Technical Officer provides technical and programmatic support for malaria prevention and case management at both facility and community levels in high-endemic sectors

Under the technical guidance of the Senior Malaria Advisors and Senior Community Health Technical Officers, the role involves coordinating malaria-related activities across supported districts and sectors.

The Malaria and Community Technical Officer contribute to the design, implementation, monitoring, and evaluation of evidence-based and sustainable malaria interventions, ensuring alignment with national policies and strategies while supporting the timely achievement of project deliverables

Responsibilities

Technical Support:

  • Work closely with the Senior Community Health Officer and the Senior Malaria Technical Officer to implement malaria and community health interventions at facility and community levels, including Integrated Community Case Management (iCCM), Home-Based Management of Malaria (HBM/HBMM), and other community-based malaria services.

  • Plan and coordinate implementation of malaria and community health activities in close collaboration with the Rwanda Biomedical Center (RBC), including MOPDD, MCCH, Community Health Program, and with District health counterparts.

  • Support facility and community-levels implementation of the Multiple First-line Therapies (MFT) strategy by ensuring CHWs and facility providers understand and follow national MFT guidelines, monitoring basic adherence to ACT allocation, and coordinating with district and RMS counterparts to maintain availability of MFT-related malaria commodities.

  • Conduct Training of Trainers (ToTs) and trainings for health care providers, Community and Environmental Health Officers (CEHOs), and Community Health Workers (CHWs) on malaria case management, malaria in pregnancy (MiP), iCCM, HBM, and other community malaria technical areas, including on-the-job training and mentorship.

  • Support capacity-building of CHWs and health facility staff to strengthen malaria prevention, diagnosis, treatment, and referral in line with national guidelines.

  • Collaborate with RISE Malaria & Emerging Infectious Diseases Mentors to support the implementation of targeted malaria interventions in malaria hotspots.

  • Organize and coordinate supportive supervision and mentorship for malaria and community health activities at both facility and community levels, ensuring adherence to national standards and protocols.

  • Monitor the implementation of project work plan activities related to malaria and community health, ensuring progress and timely execution of activities at district and sector levels.

  • In collaboration with Senior Malaria Officer and senior Community Health officer, develop and monitor learning, documentation, and knowledge-sharing activities related to malaria and community health interventions.

  • Lead efforts to translate program data and findings into programmatic recommendations, operational guidance, and policy inputs to strengthen malaria and community health programming.

  • Prepare and coordinate distribution of training materials, job aids, and supplies in collaboration with the procurement and logistics teams, ensuring timely delivery to target sites.

  • Update the supervisor on field findings, identify implementation challenges, propose solutions, and monitor corrective actions.

  • Support the organization of meetings, trainings, workshops, field visits, and other project activities at district level.

  • Contribute to project work plans, budgets, and technical reports as required by supervisors or donors.

  • Assist finance staff with preparation of financial forms for advances/reimbursements, and review and reconciliation of payment documentation related to malaria and community health activities.

  • Document successful approaches, tools, and best practices in malaria and community health to inform scale-up and learning.

  • Perform any other programmatic or administrative duties assigned by the supervisor.

Reporting, Learning and Documentation:

  • Document malaria activities and assist with identification of best practices at health centers and community levels.

  • Document successes, lessons learned and challenges in implementation as well as reports of project activities and results to the project and donor, including routine quarterly and annual reports and other reporting requirements as requested, in a timely manner.

  • Collaborate with Data use & M&E to ensure that the learnings from the project implementation are being tracked and information analyzed to inform the changes being brought in the project.

  • Author/co-author abstracts, presentations, and articles for journals and conferences

Representation in Technical meetings/Discussions :

  • Represent RISE project/Jhpiego in relevant meetings organized by supported Districts.

  • Participate in technical meetings with MOH/RBC and other partner meetings as may be requested from time to time.

  • Present updates on community health and Malaria in internal quarterly technical meetings or as may be requested by supervisor.

Required Qualifications

  • Bachelor‚Äôs Degree in Nursing Sciences, Bachelor‚Äôs Degree in Clinical medicine and community health or Bachelor‚Äôs degree in Public health with background in nursing.

  • Strong requirement of valid and current license to practice from relevant bodies (Rwanda Council of Nurses, Midwives (NCNM) or Rwanda Allied Health Professions Council (RAHPC).

  • Additional trainings related to Malaria or Community Health and project planning and management

  • Experience training in IMCI, Malaria case management and iCCM

  • Minimum of 5 years of experience implementing health-related activities and programs.

  • Previous experience in Malaria, iCCM and community health implementation projects

  • Ability to cultivate strong collaboration with other team members and key stakeholders.

  • Experience with a mix of practical technical skills in malaria necessary for strengthening Malaria service delivery at national, clinical and community-level.

  • Skilled in Malaria surveillance, M&E and at least two or more of the following technical areas: strengthening service delivery programs, training, pre-service education, performance and quality improvement.

  • Demonstrated in-depth understanding of Rwandan healthcare system, particularly the public health system.

  • Experience in living and working in Rwanda preferred.

  • Familiarity with USG regulations, compliance and reporting procedures and systems

  • Ability to coach, mentor and develop technical capacity in national programs and technical staff.

  • Language requirement: (Fluent) speaking/reading English, French and Kinyarwanda is preferred.

  • Computer literacy in MS Office applications including Word, Excel, Power Point, and Outlook.

  • Willingness to travel 50-60% of working time.

Application submission deadline: 24th December 2025

Note:

The position is on a national contract and only applicants holding permit to work in Rwanda can apply. Only shortlisted candidates will receive an invitation for an interview. For further information about Jhpiego, visit our website at

www.jhpiego.org

. The successful candidate selected for this position will be subject to a pre-employment background investigation.

Jhpiego is an Affirmative Action/Equal Opportunity Employer:

Jhpiego, a Johns Hopkins University affiliate, is an equal opportunity employer and does not discriminate based on gender, marital status,pregnancy, race, color, ethnicity, national origin, age, disability, religion, sexual orientation, gender identity or expression, veteran status, other legally protected characteristics or any other occupationally irrelevant criteria. Jhpiego promotes Affirmative Action for minorities, women, individuals who are disabled, and veterans.

Recruitment scams & fraud warning

  • Jhpiego has become aware of scams involving false job offers. Please be advised:

  • Recruiters will never ask for a fee during any stage of the recruitment process.

  • All active jobs are advertised directly on our careers page.

  • Official Jhpiego emails will always arrive from a @Jhpiego.org email address. Please report any suspicious communications to

    Info@jhpiego.org

title: HR Business Intelligence Analyst at RwandAir
description:
RwandAir Ltd is the flag carrier airline of Rwanda. It operates domestic and international services to East Africa, Central Africa, West Africa, Southern Africa, Europe and the Middle East from its main base at Kigali International Airport. Our mission is to provide unsurpassed, safe, and reliable services in air transportation, including strategically linking Rwanda with the outside world while ensuring a fair return on investment. As part of the expansion strategy, we are looking for interested, qualified, and competent candidates to fill the following position:

Job Title:             HR Business Intelligence Analyst

Reports to:         Senior Manager, HR Systems & Services

Department:    HR & Administration

Location:             Kigali International Airport

 

Job Purpose

Serve as the subject matter expert in HR analytics and automation, championing a data-driven culture across the organization. This role transforms complex workforce data into actionable insights that inform strategic HR and business decisions, drive operational excellence, and enhance employee experience. By leading the design and implementation of advanced analytics, predictive models, and automation solutions, the role empowers HR and business leaders to make evidence-based decisions, fosters analytics capability across teams, and ensures the organization remains at the forefront of people analytics innovation.

 

1.      Key Duties and Responsibilities:

a)     Operational

¬∑        Design, develop, and maintain HR dashboards and reports using business intelligence tools, providing real-time insights on workforce metrics, trends, and performance indicators.

¬∑        Build and maintain robust data models, dashboards, and reporting frameworks that enable self-service analytics and democratize access to workforce insights.

¬∑        Design and implement predictive analytics models for workforce planning, including turnover prediction, succession planning readiness, talent pipeline analytics, attrition risk analysis, performance prediction, and recruitment forecasting.

¬∑        Conduct advanced statistical analysis to identify patterns, correlations, and insights that inform HR strategy and decision-making.

¬∑        In collaboration with IT, develop and maintain automated workflows within the ERP system to streamline HR processes such as onboarding, leave management, and employee lifecycle events.

¬∑        Collaborate with the IT department to integrate HR systems and ensure seamless data flow between platforms.

¬∑        Monitor system performance and optimize automation scripts for maximum efficiency.

¬∑        Ensure data quality and integrity through automated validation rules, exception reporting, and regular data audits.

¬∑        Develop automated compliance reporting to ensure adherence to labor laws, regulations, and internal policies.

¬∑        Ensure data integrity, privacy, and compliance with all relevant policies and regulations.

¬∑        Lead HR analytics projects from requirements gathering through implementation and change management.

¬∑       Act as a strategic advisor to HR and business leaders, translating workforce data into actionable insights that inform talent strategy, organizational design, and employee experience.

¬∑        Measure and report on the impact of analytics initiatives, continuously seeking opportunities to improve processes and outcomes.

¬∑        Partner with HR Business Partners to understand analytics needs and deliver customized insights that support business unit objectives.

¬∑        Collaborate with the HR Digital & Employee Experience Specialist and HR Employee Services team to ensure analytics and automation enhance the overall employee journey and improve service delivery.

¬∑        Present data insights and recommendations to senior leadership, translating complex analytics into actionable business strategies.

¬∑        Mentor and coach HR team members in analytics best practices, fostering a culture of data- driven decision-making.

¬∑        Train and support HR team members in using analytics tools and interpreting data insights.

¬∑        Drive adoption of analytics tools and insights through effective communication, training, and change management.

¬∑        Serve as subject matter expert for HR analytics, lead through influence and drive data analytics adoption across HR and business teams.

¬∑        Mentor HR members on data literacy and analytical thinking.

¬∑        Build analytics capability within the team and act as a trusted advisor, not just a technical expert.

¬∑        Lead cross-functional projects involving multiple stakeholders and systems.

¬∑        Stay current with industry trends in HR analytics, automation technologies, and artificial intelligence applications in HR.

¬∑        Perform other department duties related to the position as directed by the Head of department.

 

b)     Personal Development

¬∑        Take responsibility for own ongoing personal development and growth of expertise.

¬∑        Keep abreast with any market trends and developments.

2.      About You ‚Äì Minimum Standard Qualifications;

Bachelor's Degree in Mathematics, Statistics or Equivalent.

Essential

¬∑        Minimum 3 years of experience in HR analytics, business intelligence, or data analysis.

¬∑        Proven experience developing dashboards and reports using BI tools (Tableau, or Power BI).

¬∑        Demonstrated experience in process automation using RPA tools, workflow automation, or scripting languages.

¬∑        Strong ability to learn and understand HR processes, metrics, and KPIs across the employee lifecycle.

¬∑        Experience with SQL and data manipulation for complex queries and data extraction.

¬∑        Track record of delivering automation solutions that resulted in measurable efficiency gains.

Preferred

¬∑        Master's degree in Data Science, Business Analytics, Information Systems, or related field

¬∑        Professional certification in analytics (e.g., Tableau BI Certified: Table Data Analyst or Microsoft Certified: Data Analyst Associate).

¬∑        Experience with machine learning and predictive modelling techniques.

¬∑        Experience with ERP systems (e.g., Microsoft Dynamics 365).

 

3.      About You ‚Äì Other Desired Competencies & Skills; Job Specific Skills:

Essential

title: Monitoring, Evaluation, Accountability and Learning (MEAL) Assistant at International Alert
description:
Job Title: Monitoring, Evaluation, Accountability and Learning (MEAL) Assistant

Grade: 5
Location: Rwanda (based in Kigali with extensive field travel)
Reports to: M&E Manager
Contract Duration: One-year renewable
Management Responsibility: None
Organization: International Alert

About International Alert

International Alert is a global peacebuilding organization with over 30 years of experience supporting people affected by conflict to find peaceful, non-violent solutions. The organization works closely with communities, partners, policymakers, and businesses to address the root causes of conflict and promote sustainable peace.

Job Purpose

The MEAL Assistant supports the Rwanda Programme‚Äôs monitoring, evaluation, accountability, and learning systems. The role provides technical MEAL support to program staff and partners, ensures data quality and accuracy, supports learning and accountability processes, and contributes to evidence-based programme management in line with International Alert policies and peacebuilding frameworks.

Key Duties & Responsibilities

1. Results Monitoring & Programme Quality

  • Support integration of MEAL activities into project proposals and implementation plans.

  • Assist with MEAL plans, indicator tracking tools, and monitoring frameworks.

  • Support quarterly reviews and project close-out meetings to promote learning and best practices.

  • Track activity quality benchmarks and support quality programming.

  • Conduct basic data analysis (e.g., frequencies, simple inferential statistics).

2. Evaluations, Research & Assessments

  • Support baselines, needs assessments, research, and evaluations.

  • Help document findings and ensure quality analysis.

  • Track implementation of evaluation and research recommendations.

  • Ensure peacebuilding and conflict-sensitivity standards are upheld.

3. Data Management

  • Set up simple data management systems for trainings, events, advocacy, research, and evaluations.

  • Support project databases, data screening, accuracy tracking, and reporting.

4. Accountability Mechanisms

  • Support community accountability mechanisms (feedback boxes, incident monitoring, feedback sessions).

  • Record, document, and follow up on feedback.

  • Promote transparency by sharing key project information with stakeholders.

5. Learning & Capacity Building

  • Compile lessons learned and best practices.

  • Support knowledge-sharing workshops and learning sessions.

  • Assist with MEL staff induction and mentoring of partner CSO staff.

  • Conduct MEL trainings for program and partner staff on quality standards, peacebuilding tools, gender, entrepreneurship, and business-for-peace resources.

Travel Requirements

  • Extensive travel to districts outside Kigali and other locations as required.

Person Specification

Essential Requirements

  • Bachelor‚Äôs degree (BSc/BA) in Statistics, Social Sciences, Development Studies, Peace Studies, or a related field.

  • Significant experience in a MEAL role in post-conflict or post-genocide settings.

  • Experience managing project databases.

  • Strong monitoring, evaluation, and reporting skills.

  • Experience in training and capacity building.

  • Commitment to community participation approaches.

  • Strong analytical and communication skills.

  • Ability to write clear, evidence-based reports.

  • Professional-level French, with good working knowledge of English.

  • Self-motivated and able to work with minimal supervision.

Desirable Requirements

  • Fluency in English and French.

  • Knowledge of other Great Lakes region languages, especially Swahili.

Application Procedure

  • Submit the attached application form only (no CV or extra documents).

  • Deadline: 6 February 2026 at 5:00 PM (Kigali time)

  • Email: Rwanda@international-alert.org

  • Email Subject: Application ‚Äì MEAL Assistant

Important Notes

  • This is a local position.

  • Only shortlisted candidates will be contacted.

  • International Alert is a member of the Misconduct Disclosure Scheme (MDS), and applicants must consent to checks.

About Ntare Louisenlund School (Rwanda)

Ntare Louisenlund School (Rwanda) is on a mission to become Africa‚Äôs leading secondary school, championing academic excellence and forward-looking education. Through its innovative Plus-STEM program, the school seeks to attract top talent in mathematics, natural sciences, computer science, and technology from Rwanda and across East Africa‚Äînurturing the next generation of innovators, entrepreneurs, and global changemakers.

The school sits on a 60-hectare campus in Bugesera District, only a 45-minute drive from Kigali, and is designed to accommodate up to 1,000 boarding students. Its international academic structure prepares learners for competitive scholarships at prestigious universities worldwide. Students are enrolled in two distinct pathways:

  • IB Plus-STEM and STEM Excellence Streams (scholarship-based and assessment-selected)

  • IB Star Entrepreneurship Stream (fee-paying students from across Africa)

As the school works toward candidacy as an IB World School, it currently offers the IB Middle Years Programme and plans to introduce the IB Diploma Programme in 2028.

Ntare Louisenlund School is operated by Ntare Louisenlund CBC in partnership with Stiftung Louisenlund, a German institution with over 75 years of expertise in operating world-class boarding schools. A strategic collaboration with the Government of Rwanda is also in development to select scholarship-eligible Plus-STEM students.

The Admissions Officer will support the Director of Admissions, PR & Marketing in managing the complete admissions process while helping strengthen the school‚Äôs public image through creative content production. title: PPC Manager / Country PPC Head at Spiro
description:
JOB VACANCY ANNOUNCEMENT

Position Title: PPC Manager / Country PPC Head

Department: Production Planning & Control (PPC)
Reports To: Global Head of Manufacturing
Duty Station: Kenya / Uganda / Rwanda / Nigeria (Country Plant Level)
Employment Type: Full-Time

Position Overview

The Country PPC Head is responsible for end-to-end Production Planning & Control (PPC) activities at the country-level assembly plant. The role ensures accurate demand planning, effective MRP execution, disciplined production scheduling, inventory control, and timely ERP reporting.

The position works closely with the Global Head ‚Äì PPC to ensure strict adherence to global PPC standards, accurate system transactions, and smooth coordination across production, supply chain, and finance teams.

Key Responsibilities

1. Country-Level PPC Leadership

  • Lead PPC operations at the country plant in alignment with global PPC strategy.

  • Prepare weekly and monthly production plans based on sales forecasts, inventory levels, and plant capacity.

  • Ensure compliance with standardized global PPC processes and planning discipline.

2. Demand Planning & MRP Execution

  • Collect, validate, and translate sales forecasts into material and production requirements.

  • Execute MRP runs and ensure:

    • Planned orders are generated for all demand.

    • Planned orders are reviewed, adjusted, and converted into production orders or purchase requisitions.

  • Resolve MRP exceptions to ensure timely material availability.

3. Production Order Management

  • Create, release, and prioritize production orders based on capacity, material availability, and delivery commitments.

  • Monitor daily order progress and communicate risks or delays to the Global Head ‚Äì PPC.

4. Material Management & Inventory Control

  • Ensure timely posting of component goods issues (GI) to inventory and general ledger.

  • Maintain optimal inventory levels to avoid stock-outs and excess inventory.

  • Coordinate with warehouse teams for material issuance, kitting, and staging.

  • Support physical stock counts and cycle counting activities.

5. Production Execution & ERP Confirmation

  • Ensure accurate ERP posting for:

    • Production confirmations

    • Finished Goods (FG) receipts

  • Validate WIP accuracy, consumption posting, and batch traceability.

  • Ensure all production transactions are closed daily.

6. Order Settlement & Cost Tracking

  • Ensure production orders are settled and posted to the general ledger within required timelines.

  • Coordinate with Finance on production variances, consumption accuracy, and cost analysis.

  • Report deviations and abnormalities to the Global Head ‚Äì PPC.

7. Master Data Management

  • Maintain accuracy of plant-level master data, including:

    • Bills of Materials (BOMs)

    • Routings

    • Work centers

    • Cycle times and capacities

  • Provide feedback to global master data teams for corrections and improvements.

8. Coordination & Reporting

  • Work closely with production, quality, warehouse, procurement, and finance teams.

  • Participate in global PPC review meetings and present country-level performance.

  • Maintain and submit:

    • Daily production vs. plan dashboards

    • Inventory health and shortage reports

    • Weekly MRP status and exception reports

9. People Management

  • Lead and mentor the country PPC team.

  • Train staff on ERP usage, MRP processes, and planning accuracy.

  • Implement global PPC process standardization at the plant level.

Required Qualifications & Experience

  • Bachelor‚Äôs degree in Mechanical, Production, or Industrial Engineering.

  • Minimum 10 years of experience in Production Planning & Control within automotive, engineering, manufacturing, or EV industries.

  • Strong hands-on experience with MRP systems and ERP platforms (SAP, Odoo, Oracle, MS Dynamics, or similar).

  • Solid understanding of BOMs, routings, scheduling, and inventory control.

  • Strong analytical skills with proficiency in Excel and planning tools.

  • Excellent communication and coordination abilities.

Preferred Qualification:

  • MBA in Operations Management or Supply Chain Management.

Key Performance Indicators (KPIs)

  • Production schedule adherence

  • Material availability rate

  • MRP execution accuracy

  • Inventory Days on Hand (DOH) and inventory turnover

  • Production order closure and settlement cycle time

  • WIP and finished goods inventory accuracy

  • Compliance with global PPC processes

How to Apply

Interested and qualified candidates are invited to submit their applications via email:

title: Tender Notice for Refurbishment of Urugo Women Opportunity Center (WOC)
description:
TENDER NOTICE FOR REFURBISHMENT OF URUGO WOMEN OPPORTUNITY CENTER (WOC) 

Tender Reference: URUGO/REFURB/2025efurbishment
Issue Date: December 5, 2025
Closing Date: December 14, 2025

1. Introduction

Urugo Women‚Äôs and Opportunity Center (WOC) invites qualified interior designers, contractors, and refurbishing firms to submit proposals for the refurbishment and upgrade of the Urugo WOC facilities, including interior spaces and garden improvements.

The purpose of this tender is to identify a capable service provider who can deliver high-quality design, renovation works, and garden enhancement within the required timeline and according to Urugo‚Äôs standards.

2. Scope of Work

The refurbishment project includes, but is not limited to:

2.1 Interior Refurbishment

  • Redesign and upgrade of selected interior spaces

  • Decorative enhancements and spatial improvements

  • Furniture procurement or refurbishment

  • Technical works (painting, carpentry, masonry, electrical adjustments where needed)

  • Coordination of all related labour and materials

2.2 Garden Upgrade

Bidders must include a separate fee estimate and proposed concept for the garden upgrade, covering:

  • Landscaping improvements

  • Outdoor furniture or decorative additions

  • Pathway or layout adjustments

  • Any other proposed aesthetic or functional improvements

3. Project Timeline Requirements

Bidders must clearly outline:

  1. Availability and Time Allocation

    • Explanation of how the bidder will allocate time and resources to ensure the project is completed by the end of January.

  2. Estimated Start and Completion Dates

    • Proposed start date

    • Estimated project duration and key milestones

  1. Financial Proposal

The financial proposal must include:

  1. Comprehensive Fees

    • Breakdown of design fees

    • Labour and contractor costs

    • Material costs (if applicable)

    • Garden upgrade fees

  2. Transport & Logistics

    • Indicate whether transportation to and from the site is included in the proposed fees.

  3. Labour Team Payment Structure

    • Specify whether labour costs are calculated on a daily rate or project-based structure.

5. Contractors and Labour Team Requirements

Bidders must provide clear information on:

  • Whether they work with their own contractors or manual labourers

  • Whether labour will be sourced from Kayonza district or brought from Kigali

  • Roles and responsibilities of each team member

  • Whether the bidder will supervise all technical work personally, or if a project manager will be assigned

6. Procurement & Materials

Proposals must specify:

  • Whether the bidder will source and purchase materials directly, or if Urugo WOC must support procurement

  • Details of any preferred suppliers for materials, d√©cor, furniture, or equipment

  • Expected lead times for materials procurement

7. Maintenance & After-Care Expectations

Bidders must outline:

  • Availability for post-project follow-up

  • Any provided maintenance guidance or support

  • Optional after-care services and related fees (if applicable)

8. Submission Requirements

Interested bidders should submit the following documents:

  1. Technical Proposal

    • Work plan and methodology

    • Timeline and implementation schedule

    • Design approach and proposed concepts

    • Team structure and responsibilities

  2. Financial Proposal (separate document)

    • Itemized cost breakdown

    • Payment schedule

    • Transport and logistics information

  3. Portfolio and Experience

    • Examples of previous similar projects

    • References from 3 past clients

  4. Legal and Administrative Documents

    • Business registration

    • Tax clearance certificates

    • RSSB clearance certificate

    • RDB certificate

9. Submission Instructions

All proposals must be submitted physically to Urugo WOC not later than December 14, 2025.

Late submissions will not be considered.

10. Evaluation Criteria

Proposals will be evaluated based on:

  • Technical soundness and feasibility

  • Experience and portfolio quality

  • Cost-effectiveness

  • Team capacity and supervision structure

  • Timeline suitability

  • Approach to materials procurement and logistics

  • Clarity of garden upgrade proposal

title: Manager, Commercial Business Intelligence at RwandAir Ltd
description:
Manager, Commercial Business Intelligence at RwandAir Ltd

Location: Kigali International Airport (KIA), Rwanda
Job Type: Full-time
Deadline: January 13, 2026

Job Overview
RwandAir Ltd, the flag carrier airline of Rwanda, is seeking a Manager, Commercial Business Intelligence to lead its commercial analytics function. The role will provide actionable insights, reporting frameworks, and performance monitoring to support data-driven decision-making across sales, network, pricing, distribution, loyalty, and customer experience.

Key Responsibilities

  • Lead the design and delivery of commercial performance dashboards and automated reporting tools.

  • Collaborate with Finance, Revenue Accounting, Sales, Marketing, and RM teams to ensure accurate revenue reporting, forecasting, and variance analysis.

  • Provide executive-level insights, scenario planning, and strategic support for route launches, network expansion, pricing, and new commercial initiatives.

  • Maintain data integrity across airline commercial systems (PSS/DCS, MIDT, CRM, BI tools) and ensure compliance with governance standards.

  • Monitor commercial KPIs, benchmark performance against industry peers, and support ad hoc strategic projects.

  • Drive adoption of BI tools and provide training and capacity building for end users.

Qualifications & Experience

  • Bachelor‚Äôs degree in Statistics, Economics, Data Science, Business Analytics, Finance, or related field.

  • 7‚Äì10 years‚Äô experience in Business Intelligence, Data Analytics, or Commercial Analytics, preferably in the airline industry.

  • Proficiency in BI tools (Power BI, Tableau, Qlik) and experience with airline commercial systems (PSS/DCS, MIDT, BSP, CRM).

  • Strong financial modelling, forecasting, and commercial performance measurement skills.

  • Familiarity with SQL, large datasets, and data quality management.

  • Strong analytical skills and ability to translate data into actionable insights.
